title: Help You Out
extra:
One of Greg Lato's ambitions for his music career in general, is to be the kind of artist capable of indulging all of his creative influences, to change his colors with each project without losing his cache as a true indie pop artist. According to Motif magazine, Lato's "Rhode Island's next great pop recording artist."

His latest EP, aptly titled DO THE BEST WITH WHAT I GOT, recorded mostly in LA with co-writer/producer Jim McGorman (Avril Lavigne, Weezer, Cher) and co-writer/producer Steve Catizone over a two-month period, is the sound of Lato indulging the entire spectrum of his creative senses, from dance grooves to silky smoothness to proud power pop with hooks the size of Hoboken.

The music video for "JUST ANOTHER GOODBYE" has also been gaining traction and accumulating views in big chunks on YouTube (over 116,000 views!!) and Facebook, and is being aired on TV networks in USA and Canada (HD Net and the Cool TV). The video has also been added to over 1000 health and fitness clubs worldwide, and over 25,000 nightclubs, restaurants and retailers including Macy's and Ikea stores. Like its predecessors "Beautiful Woman" and "Monday Morning Breakdown," "Just Another Goodbye" boasts a brilliant arrangement-strings, vocal harmonies, modern tech flourishes-to go along with its elaborate videography, and one uber-sexy model.
The song has also recently been placed in the feature film '16-Love', starring Lindsey Shaw from Pretty Little Liars and Chandler Massey from Days of our Lives which was nationwide in theaters in Jan 2012. The film also went to #1 on iTunes movie charts and spent 8 consecutive months in the top 10!!

Greg also writes for and develops other artists through his Talent Planning and Development company PUSH POP ENTERTAINMENT, has received awards from the Billboard World Song Contest, and written for MTV and A&E network shows.

Greg has also co-written the theme song for the Gloria Gemma Breast Cancer Foundation titled 'I'LL GIVE YOUR WEAK MY STRENGTH' performed by Rob Marin and Kelley Lennon, which debuted in 2012 at their monumental Flames of Hope celebration and was featured in the PBS special 'Behind the Ribbon' in May 2013.

'HELP YOU OUT' is the powerful and attitude-driven single written by Greg and produced by Rich Mercurio/Lee Nadel, it boasts a brilliant arrangement mixing 80's Nile Rodgers with Rob Thomas pop sensibilities. The music video, just released in April 2012, already has over 110,000 views on YouTube!!

The anticipated new single 'THERE'S A SONG FOR THAT' written by Greg, produced by Rich Mercurio/Lee Nadel and mixed/mastered by Brian Malouf is out now. It has a universal theme of all the many things there is a song for, and the fact that everyone has a song that makes someone think of them. People from 8 to 80 can relate, when a certain song plays, there is a moment, time and place that evokes a memory which gives that song a special meaning in everyone's life.
The music video, released in April 2013, already has over 136,000 views!!

title: Party's Over (Alternative Mix)
extra: Oliver Shaw is an Oxford-based songwriter, performer and producer. His main project Worldview aims to fuse the sounds of Indie and Dance music with insightful lyrics reminiscent of Elvis Costello or Morrissey and the melodic sensibility of the classic 60âs acts. Oliver began playing in bands, including one with Coldplayâs bassist-to-be, then spent several years honing a one-man band approach in his studio, writing, singing, recording and playing everything in the manner of Stevie Wonder, early Prince or World Party. He self-released a debut album, the relationship-themed âWar Yearsâ, in late 2002, culled from home sessions. It enjoyed some airplay and praise for the âtimeless qualityâ of the songwriting. A second set, âPaying For Itâ, followed in January 2005, with a more diverse stylistic palette and topics ranging from celebrity and consumerism to the Iraq conflict. The Oxfordbands.com website judged it âchock full of good tunes, clever lyrics andâ¦united by a consistent, if rather misanthropic, musical visionâ. As well as gaining FM and online radio exposure his tracks were featured on various unsigned compilation CDs. He appeared many times at major Oxford venues with a backing band from the ranks of other fledging local acts, and played some solo acoustic sets at London venues. Oliver then put together a new gigging line-up of Worldview, combining live instruments and PC, playing dates in Oxford and London, and an album, âOur Conditionâ, is available at the iTunes store and Amazon MP3. âWorldview's aptly titled "Our Condition" takes a snapshot view of modern living, with its raw honest exploration of life today...It's a strong offering with music that combines the ballads of REM with the dance beats of Duran Duran" - Oxfordshire Music Scene. The Credit Crunch is the subject of download single, âPartyâs Overâ, which along with other Worldview tracks is a staple of Internet radio stations. It features on the new Worldview album "Schoolboy Errors", released in February 2012. Oliver also has a dance/pop songwriting/production side-project called Starmaker; the track "Another Us" was recently licensed to the Lucky Sounds label for a digital release. A third project is Desmond Chancer And The Long Memories, retro jazz-blues ballads, with two single releases on Villainous Records.

title: Anywhere But Here (2012)
extra:
Norman Lamont is a singer/songwriter from Edinburgh in Scotland; he has been gigging there with a succession of bands since the late 90s. His current band The Invisible Helpers serves up anthemic rock with gratuitous violins. This song is a re-recorded version of a song from his 2009 solo album Roadblock.

'As the cover suggests, this is a darker set of songs, with themes of mortality and loss. The title track and The Spell speak directly about these, while Anywhere But Here shows a closed-down, depressed world and Come With Me a way out of it. It's not all gloom and doom, with typical wry humour showing through in Best of the Blues, I'll Be Back and When I Came Home From Egypt.' (Roadblock review)

extra: dolylamby aka eric lamb has been writing songs most of his life. His styles vary from punk to pop-rock... from country to ambient/spoken meditation. His upbeat, danceclub 'boy meets girl' song, "Would You Like To Come Home With Me?" was nominated for 'Best Alternative Song' in the 2011 Hollywood Music in Media Awards. He presently lives in San Diego on a yacht and is working on new things.

Fast Forward
extra:
2008: Tim co-founds the band "Brand New Relic" with Rick Levey & Alex Schiro. Tech Ninja joins later as lead vocalist. They play 6 shows total.
2009: "Brand New Relic" disbands. Tim joins with the band "Thirty 2 Twenty" as the bass guitarist. They play several shows in venues across the Los Angeles area and record one album together. Tech Ninja (as "J. Whitman") is nominated for an Independent Music Award (Best Dance/Electronica Song; "Metro (feat. Samurai MX)").
2011: Tim leaves "Thirty 2 Twenty".
2012: Tim and Tech Ninja reunite to form "Echo D-Vice".

Emergency
extra:
Since forming in 2007, Richmond, VA pop rockers The Jim Ivins Band have been making a name for themselves in the Virginia area and beyond, scoring rave reviews from publications like Absolutepunk.net and Property of Zack, while also garnering artist of the month honors from MuzikDizcovery.com and artist of the day at Fanbridge.com. They have also been fortunate enough to share the stage with national acts such as Parachute, Carolina Liar, The Rocket Summer, Cracker, The Ataris, Mae, Carbon Leaf, Pat McGee Band, He Is We and Every Avenue, as well as showcasing at the 2009 Miami Music Festival. Their latest offering, 2012's Everything We Wanted, showcases a maturity and expansion of their sound, from the delicate acoustics of love song "Rollercoaster" to the frenetic rock of "Emergency" and the sexy syncopation of "Lost My Mind." Inspired by a recent show opening for rock radio favorites Switchfoot and The Airborne Toxic Event, Ivins decided to look farther inward when writing for Everything We Wanted, crafting a record soaked in introspection while touching on a myriad of emotions and situations like addiction ('The Sight Of Fire'), sex ('Lost My Mind') and moving forward after experiencing tragedy ('Everything We Wanted')."
Proving themselves to be universally appealing, in 2010 The Jim Ivins Band signed a licensing deal with MTV. Their 2009 self-titled EP was engineered and mixed by Grammy Award-winning engineer Michael Congdon and features the song "The Chance," a single produced by The Early November's Ace Enders that has caught fire on internet radio giant Pandora, racking up 160,000 spins and counting. Says Skope Magazine, "whether itâs rock you crave or pop goodness that you desire, [The Jim Ivins Band] will satisfy all of your musical needs."

title: My Toronto (Demo)
extra: Last minute track added to my Red Bull Music Academy demo and app. Took me roughly 3 1/2-4 days to create and mix. This is more of a remix of a track started 2-3 years ago. The drums and guitar samples are from the original track. The words were a last minute adlib from my brother and a guy name Joe who was interviewed during the G20 summit in Toronto. As when I got to a certain point during the making of track that I felt like I was taking a ride on Toronto Transit.

title: Dr Phil
extra: Dr Phil is a song written about the American talk show therapist. It explores how addictive his shows are, and the irony being that while he's helping guests on his show he fails to turn to the tv cameras and say to the audience to get off the couch and do something with their own lives rather than wasting time watching his show.... A light hearted commentary on the trappings of reality tv.  From Lucy B's debut album Botany St.

Damaged Goods
extra:
Work down at the factory doing quality control,
I sit and watch the conveyor belt roll.
First day of work the foreman he said,
"Listen up close to your job my friend"

(chorus)
That's damaged goods,
That's damaged goods,
That's damaged goods my friend.

Three wrong in a batch then you toss the bunch
Hell of a lot cheaper than giving refunds.
If it don't work first time then you toss it out.
We don't believe in the benefit of the doubt.

(chorus)

Looks a little funny or the color ain't right,
Throw it in the bin we don't sell them half price.
Damage just cosmetic, still can't take it home.
With new regulations those days are gone.

(chorus)

Live with my girl on the 82,
holes in the roof and the rents overdue.
Sometimes after work if we're not too tired,
we'll just sit and stare at the sky.

We could go see the ducks in the park, in the pond,
and Iâd return by the light of the moon

Come on, are you up for going?

(chorus)

Sunshine or stormy weather weâll spend the day together.

extra: Live Performance of Date With Fate..A retro song about a guy who is about to go on a date with someone he believes is his "One" or his fate. It's just a really fun song that recalls music eras of the past, the whole Fifties/Sixties crooner doo-wop vibe.

title: Shayne Stolz- Perfect Unison (original)
extra: Performance of my original song Perfect Unison on March.15,2012. It's a pop song about equality. Every genre of music is unique and special in it's own way, and we shouldn't make others feel ashamed in liking certain styles of music. Or judge them for it. No hate. Music is music, it's one in the same, it's your choice to pick whatever artist or genre you feel you can connect with. No one should ever be or feel like they cannot express themselves without negative judgment. Same with love, there should be no limits in who we can be with or what love we wish to share. In hopes that someday we will live in harmony, we will live as one, under the stars we all will live in Perfect Unison. A perfect world filled with love and happiness.

title: Cant Wait 2 Hate You- Yung Remix
extra: Nadia Yung fell in love with music at a very young age singing along to songs she would hear on the radio. At the age of 2 she had a toy keyboard & loved it ever since. She started school at the age 5 at Northwest Elementary School in a small town called Dodge City in the State of Kansas. There she officially learned to play the keyboard at the age of 6 along with other instruments. One day in her music class her teacher put on a movie about Ludwig van Beethoven. She was a little confused about his ways, such as an alcoholic & angry man. Almost completely deaf when he composed his Ninth Symphony, which was done largely in his head without being able to hear it she was truly inspired & amazed. Growing up she had many influences in music such as Shai, Jodeci, 112, Bone Thugs N Harmony, Usher, Mariah Carey, K-Ci & Jojo && many other big names in the genre r&b/pop & rap. Nadia moved to Nevada when she was 9 after the tragic death of her cousin which was 8 when he died near the Hoover Dam during a family vacation. Raised in Las Vegas, NV since 1999 the now 21 yr.old got involved with gangs at the age 11. She became a gang member of "Bloods" at the age of 13. Smoked her first joint when she was 13 not knowing in the long run she would into an addiction to other drugs. Trouble child in and out of juvenile her mother gave her up to the State & became a foster child. With so much pain & resentment she picked up a pen and notebook expressing all feelings and put her thoughts on a piece of paper. After awhile it became her way to vent. Ever since she has written over 100 songs genres r&b, hip hop, pop, rap & even country. Soon turning 22 her goal is to work with a few familiar faces in the music industry such as Drake, Rascal Flatts, Kanye West, Jamie Foxx, Bone Thugs N Harmony and many more.

Randy Bishop is an accomplished songwriter, musician and vocalist. His original songs have been used in television series, as well as radio and television commercials. Randy has performed on stage with many well-known performers over the years. He writes in the rock, pop, country and Christian genres and plays all of the instruments on his recordings, along with singing all the vocals. As a contemporary songwriter, Randy is most interested in finding other artists to perform his material on their own albums, as well as having his songs licensed for use in movies and television. Randy is a member of ASCAP.

title: A Magical time of the year - L. Egerer - K. Fairchild
Hip Shake
extra:
Paul Da Vinci started his musical career as a session singer, doing demonstration records for major songwriters, Tony Macauley, Don Black and numerous others, pitching to artists like Tom Jones and The Hollies. He sang on numerous major advertising campaigns: British Airways, Smiths Crisps etc. He then went on to appear on albums by guitarist Gary Moore, Ringo Starr, David Essex, Jeff Wayne's album Sparticus, and an album "Dear Anyone" by Don Black and Geoff Stephens. He appeared on Top of the Pops with Justin Hayward ("Forever Autumn") and Elton John ("I Guess That's Why They Call It The Blues"). In the 70's he had solo success as the legendary original voice on the Rubettes' world-wide number 1 "Sugar Baby Love", and his self produced and composed top 20 UK and European number 1 hit "Your Baby Ain't Your Baby Anymore". In the 80's he had a hit with Tight Fit, "Back To The 60's pt II" and has sold over 8 million records world-wide. He has also starred in the West End production of The Who's "Tommy" to rave reviews ("Truly Exceptional " - Time Out).

Paul's current show features the hits plus a wide range of classic music, (Motown, Swing, Rock and Pop) mainly from the 60's and 70's and featuring his amazing 3Â½ octave voice, and the showmanship you would associate with such a seasoned professional. Standing Ovations are a regular occurrence. Ask anyone who has seen him perform. Paul has recently played to capacity audiences at The Strode Theatre, Street and headlined The Somerton Arts Festival 2011, but is also performing in a wide range of venues, including intimate music venues, corporate, hotels, private functions, parties etc and has just returned from performing in Munich with the 15 piece Swing of Life Orchestra.

Paul has recently released an album of songs Da Vinci & The Justice Dept which he has sung, written, arranged and produced and is available on itunes. Paul is currently writing and producing and pitching material from his home studio.

title: When It's Over
extra:
Pimples Glue is a Pop Punk band from Indonesia. Singer and guitarist Day formed Pimples Glue in 2007 and performing in the events with many indie
bands. In 2009, the band signed a contract with a major label named Golden Musik Indo and releasing a
compilation album Highway To The Star 2. In 2010, the band joined an album Suck Me Please released by indie label from Bogor named Flashback Records. In 2011, Pimples Glue releasing some compilation albums, Still Rock Today Compilation which released by Flashback Records, Struggle Together #1 Compilation released by SCC, and Broken Cover Compilation. After all that, Pimples Glue signed with Mundix Records and released Right or wrong?! EP and at the same time The band joined a compilation album This Is How We Struggle Compilation which released by Mundix Records. In 2012, Pimples Glue released a new single titled When it's over.

We are more alike than we are different.
And if we could learn to use that concept more often - to work out our problems, maybe the world would be a happier place.
lyrics
Every little star has dreams as big as the universe
Reaching out beyond horizons never seen before,
Beyond their stratosphere.

We are really not that different.
Looking for some bigger part of life
I wonder if Iâll find it
Before my time is done
Maybe if I give up
Itâll find me, itâll find me insteadâ¦

Wishing star
Iâm a wishing star tonight
And I wish for love in this world.
Where you are
You can make the same wish too
And maybe you and I can live in harmony

See the moon that glitters so softly in the inky night
Poets, wise men, lovers
Find Le Luna inspires them to flowery words
You and I, weâre really quite the same.
Looking for some magic in our lives
I wonder if weâll find it
This thread of love that binds
If we stumble while weâre looking,
Will it find us, will it find us insteadâ¦?

title: Mad Waltz
extra:
At the age of 7 Ukrainian neo classical composer Sergey Rybytskyy was lured to the piano in a way similar to Edgar Allen Poeâs character in âThe Tell-Tale Heartâ was drawn to the heartbeat under the floor. That haunting call has never left Rybytskyy and instead of attempting to resist the attraction he allows it to run wild. In addition to this unrelenting passion Rybytskyy has taken the appropriate steps to fine tune his craft by attending multiple courses from Dnepropetrovsk Music College as well as receiving private lessons from talented musician and piano virtuoso Vladimir Skuratovsky. Rybytskyy was able to do this while essentially leading a second life as he completed engineering school and began a career to pay his bills in the mining engineer field. When Rybytskyy leaves the mining world he often enters into his own mental lair for song writing and recording.

Rybytskyyâs musical influences cover a vast range from Alice Cooper to Marty Friedman. The primary drive of his music is to create an emotional experience for the listener that is original, lively, and refined. While the music would be used mostly for soundtracks commercially Rybytskyyâs music can actually tell a story by itself. Rybytskyyâs main instrument of choice is the keyboard but there are also a variety of other instruments used which allows a wide range of synthetic and authentic sounds that create a palpable atmosphere that invites the listener to escape into the musical world that Rybytskyy has created.

Rybytskyyâs released his debut album âNew Vistaâ in 2012 to the welcoming arms of classical music, prog rock, and neo classical metal fans. The album was perceived as a work apart from the formulaic, stylistic labelings that most music in this generation falls under as the album swoons from ambient sounds to driving drums. Amped Sounds marveled at Rybytskyyâs ability to combine this wide variety of influences and genres to create a âmusical experience within itself.â Indie Music Digest stated that âNew Vista is definitely a dynamic and progressive musical statement that offers a lot of musical variety via vivid sound and brilliant creative energy.â

A signal of the fervor with which Rybytskyy approaches his artistry, he wasted no time completing a follow up album by releasing âIn Labyrinths of the Soulâ later in 2012. This album was met with adulation as well. Multiple reviews of the album mention the ease of which the listener can get lost in the album. Rybytskyy surprised the Middle Tennessee Music blog with his ability to use the keyboard to make the sounds of many instruments and have it still sound authentic. Hands Off Promotions remarked that the album sounds like âTim Burtonâs take on a classic.â

Rybytskyyâs unwavering drive will not allow him to rest. He has already been accumulating material for a third release in the near future. Future recordings of his will include prog rock versions of some of Beethoven and Bachâs compositions. Rybytskyy looks forward to the possibility of using a vocalist in some recordings as well in order to expand the diversity of his music. You will also be able to hear some of Rybytskyyâs work on television and film as he has recently signed deals with publishers and music libraries for commercial use.

title: Sea Of Trees
extra: The Aokigahara forest in Japan is one of the worlds most popular places for suicide. Translated to English it means Sea Of Trees . There are also many legends that attempt to explain why this place attracts people looking to do themselves in. I have known about these legends for a while and thought it would make a good song topic. Over the weekend i wrote and recorded this song. Just a note the forest is actually southwest of Tokyo not at the southern tip of Japan like i say in the song.  This is one of 3 mixes i did of the song. This one has the most going on . It may be better with just an acoustic mix. I went a bit crazy with drums on this. Hope you like it.

title: Sins Of The Fathers
extra: In 1987 [ yes i m dating myself] I recorded this song with my drummer friend Gene Tano in a recording studio in Columbia MD. Scott Lean was on the vocal and we had  studio help as well.  I had wrote the song a couple of years earlier  when i read a news article about a Canadian veteran who went into a government building and started shooting  at anything or anyone that moved. I mixed in  other stranger elements of horror and the book of the dead" and came up with this song that attempted to get inside the head of a terrorist  killer. The song seems even creepier now because it was pre   9/11 and  other terrorist acts that the song seems to foretell.  The sound quality  is compromised because it was recorded from a cassette to an old   CD and the downloaded to a computer..After recording the song I sent it out to producers and record company's but .nobody was interested and no one ever got to hear the song.. until now. .

title: Run Away
extra:
The Watermarks are known not only for their incendiary live performances, but also their D.I.Y. approach to recording, writing, and producing which has yielded 2 self released E.P.s and a continuing series of singles released on German Label AF-Music. These Indie rock D.I.Y. Ethics, noise-pop sensibilities, and electronic textures have lead the band to craft a unique sound where melody is the main character...a sound that is danceable and poppy yet full of loud guitars and heavy organic drums. The Watermarks reside in Houston and rarely rest from writing new material and playing live shows.

- Tracks licensed to shows on MTV, Oxygen Network, E!, ADV Anime Network, Crisis Center Houston PSA's, Mobile Videos (Verizon, ATT, T-Moblie), and The Houston Aeros.
- The Watermarks have shared the stage with bands and artists such as: Weezer, Echo & The Bunnymen, Cut Copy, The Flaming Lips, The Ting Tings, The Pains Of Being Pure At Heart, British Sea Power, IAMX, Secret Machines, Trail of Dead, Heartless Bastards, Ghostland Observatory, Suicide Girls, Film School, Octopus Project, etc.
- Nation wide college radio promotion campaign lead by Team Clermont (teamclermont.com) targeting 250+ stations in US and Canada in Summer of 09 for new EP âThoughts Like Bombsâ (released June 09). Songs in top 30 on dozens of stations nationwide.
- Several regional and National tours.

Official sites:
http://www.thewatermarks.net
http://www.facebook.com/thewatermarks
http://www.twitter.com/thewatermarks

Rev. RoYo is an eccentric, and ecstatic performer with a southern rock, country gospel style. He brings his message of Non Duality into every event by merging GLBT and Mainstream Popular Culture with Integrated Spirituality. With a soulful voice, a message of oneness, great costumes, and a wicked sense of humor, his shows and CDs emphasize love, beautiful melodies, interesting stories, and a bit of inspiration.



Rev. Roger Anthony Yolanda Mapes

was born and raised in Muscle Shoals, Alabama, The Hit Recording Capital of the World and the birthplaces of

Helen Keller and W.C. Handy.

The Muscle Shoals area is populated by an abundance of musicians and visual artists/painters. RoYo began studying music, painting and drawing at a young age with local artists and was encouraged to develop his own unique vision, which combines GLBT culture, drag performance, personal spirituality, and a love for Old Time Gospel Music. RoYo is influenced by pop, rock, blues,gospel, country, and folk, but doesnât self-consciously follow any one traditionâ¦combining them all into some hybrid of his own.

title: Lady
extra:
Tim Ruff is an acoustic singer-songwriter with a distinct smooth pop style. His soulful, life experience inspired songs of guitar with velvety vocals have quickly made their home among the bustling whispers of local coffee shops and in the top acoustic music locales throughout southeast Pennsylvania.

The undeniable uplifting quality of his melodies and his warm and friendly charm make it easy to take in his playful and poignant poetry. Through stories, love songs, and serenades, he paints true emotion that his listeners can relate to on many levels.

Originating from Chesterton, Indiana, Tim currently resides in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, where his music regularly fills the rooms of popular music venues including: The Three Rivers Arts Festival, Club CafÃ©, and the Shadow Lounge.

Tim is currently working on his first full-length album, which will be released in the early fall of 2012.

title: Young Dev- Can You Handle It
My Life in Pictures      (5/21/12 Dan Skye Master)
extra:
Hey everyone! Thanks for stopping by. I'm Glenn and I'm a songwriter from Princeton, New Jersey (in the U.S.). With my trusty sidekick Chloe the Chihuahua by my side, I've been writing songs for many years now and it's my favorite thing in the world. I sincerely appreciate you checking out the tunes and I hope you like what you hear. Thanks for Your Time! Yours in Music, Glenn Page


About "My Life in Pictures":

Hey everyone - thanks for checking out my latest single, "My Life in Pictures." I'm endlessly inspired by the topics of memory and loss, and the basic idea for this song stemmed from, of all things, a friend's digital picture frame (the kind that changes the image every few seconds).

It made me think of the ways we try to freeze moments in our lives and hold onto them and keep them alive in the present, even when they're no longer an accurate representation of the past.

It also made me think about, with the advent of things like youtube, the ways we are documenting more and more of our pasts almost to the point where the past and present are existing simultaneously. Of course, if you spend your present living in the past, what will you look back on in the future when you think about today?

I'm very proud of this song, and I hope you enjoy it as well.

Thanks, Glenn Page 4/9/12

title: Cruisin' With My Baby Tonight
extra:
Click Here To Buy

Cruisin' With My Baby Tonight has just been nominated to be part of Tunecore's compilation album "25 Songs Of Summer"! Complimentary mp3 download available at Amazon as a free download until Labor Day.

Bruce Berghâs newest 2012 release, âNight Lifeâ is a collection of original âRat-Packâ tunes written during 2011 as a nightlife entertainer in some of Chicagoâs finest dining establishments. Bergh performs on piano with vocal stylings in the Pop, Rock and Jazz Vocal genres. As a composer, he strives for memorable melody lines accompanied by jazz harmonizations with a positive message.

Bergh studied at Sherwood Music School and the University of Chicago, and has written hundreds of songs, commercial music and jingles, as well as arranged music for a large number of clients through the years at his three recording studios. As a professor of Music Technology, Bergh taught in four universities, done clinician work for MTNA, MENC, and NAMM conventions, and founded The Bergh Institute of Music Technology (BIMT.net and DrMIDI.com).

Some of Berghâs career highlights include playing organ for the Chicago Cubs at Wrigley Field, performing live with Kerry Livgren of âKansasâ on synthesizer, pianist/vocalist for Willow Creek Community Chapel events, traveling North America as a product specialist and clinician for numerous musical instrument manufacturers, collaborating with Bob Moog & Ray Kurzweil regarding synthesizer technology and sales, and leading worship and performing in many top churches, theaters and convention centers across the United States.


Bruce Berghâs Discography:

"25 Songs of Summer" compilation album released by Tunecore on iTunes Memorial Day 2012

âNight Lifeâ a CD collection of new âRat-Packâ styled and pop originals released April 28, 2012

âTaxi Portfolio 2011â is an eclectic collection of tunes written for Taxi A&R in 2011

âChristmas Time of the Yearâ a CD collection of Christmas originals released in November 2011

âChristmas Time of the Yearâ a single released on iTunes 2010

âFamily Albumâ a CD collection of music written about his family released in 2010 as an Independent Artist

âParadiseâ a CD collection of original Contemporary Christian (CCM) songs released in 2009 by BIMT Studios.

âBody Language: An Excercise in Excessive Sampling Abuseâ a 45 single released in 1988 by Rednose Records (Flip side of "Dubois Boys")

"Dubois Boys" a Novelty Polka 45 RPM single released in 1988 by Rednose Records

title: Lucky Me
extra:
when i wake up in the morning,
i hear the trees blow back and fourth,
i want to live that way, and dance in the rain,
let me tell you, we're gonna find some better days,

so lovely to dance in the rain,

i can't tell you what you're thinking,
no, i can't read your mind,
but i find your silence to be remarkable,
there's no reason for us to say too much,

i'm so lucky to have someone like you,
so lucky to sing by the moon,
i'm so lucky to have a girl like you,
so lucky to kiss by the moon,

i've gone astray in some mindless tangents,
yeah, i've been strolling back and fourth,
but honey, i'll return for you sometime soon,
and give you all that you deserve,

i'm so lucky to have someone like you,
so lucky to sing by the moon,
i'm so lucky to have a girl like you,
so lucky to kiss by the moon,
yes i'm so lucky to have a girl like you,
so lucky to sing by the moon
i'm so lucky to know this is where i belong,
so lovely to dance in the rain.

title: The Weight I Kept Waiting (basement demo)
extra:
the devil sold me a date with the sunlight
but i traded it back for a stab at the night
and when he asked
"why you looking so down boy?"
I told him, "i can't explain"
but my god, my god, my god
this is all my fault
i'm caught in a knot
of all i've been taught
but i've never learned
just how to apply it
now i'm making a deal
with you and your friends
to finally know
how far my heart can bend
and now my back is sore
from the weight i kept waiting
I made a deal with myself
to never lose touch
with my friends and family
but when i think about the way things are right now
all i know is
my god, my god, my god
i have got to move on
i'll be lost in a trance
of song and dance
i'm starting a band
inside of the city
i'm making some moves
a brand new start
i'm off to test the depths of my heart
and i'll be singing this song
so that the singers keep singing
my back is sore from the weight i kept waiting
my heart is cold from the love i stopped loving
my eyes are wide from the trust i stopped trusting
and i'll be singing this song so that the singers keep singing

title: Get Away
extra:
i ain't articulate
i've got two sides
i hate to say that this will all go by
so keep your pictures
and your carpet stains
now listen closely to the quiet rain
i drove my car
down to the city lights
i left the scene
i freed up my time
i met the folks i thought i needed to
but i always seem to roll right back to you
to get away
yeah, to get away
to get away
to get away
you never see the beauty
of the hills in your face
till you park your car
and make a home of the place
it always gets old
when you're waiting around
till you're driving away
looking back on the town
i listened to the demons
and i followed their steps
i told myself to hurry get it off of my face
i traded all my teeth in exchange for a hit
i had a bone to pick
so i just blamed it on the gun
i got away
yeah, i got away
i got away
i got away

extra:
Stephen Nichols- Trombonist / Vocalist / Bandleader / Composer / Arranger began his professional music career in 1967 with the organization of his first music group, Made In America. As a bandleader Mr. Nichols conducted and performed with groups in the USA including Hawaii and in Europe, Canada, the Caribbean and Asia. Steve's career, for over forty years, has been most interesting.
He has performed on stage with Sammy Davis Jr., Stevie Wonder, The Glenn Miller Orchestra, The Fifth Dimension, The Osmond Brothers, The Michel LeGrand Orchestra, The Red Skelton Show, The Del Courtney Orchestra, The Luther Ingram Show, The Chita Rivera Show. The Crystal Gale Show, The Marvin Hammlisch Show, The Ben Vereen Show, The Patti Andrews Show, Royal Carribean Cruise Lines, Princess Cruises, Holland America Line, Celebrity Cruises among many, many other international performances.
Stephen Nichols was Principal / featured Trombonist on National and International tours with The Mantovani Orchestra and served as trombonist with the U.S. Air Force White House Band where he performed for Presidents and Heads Of State from many nations worldwide.
Steve has traveled over a million miles and performed for millions of people in live stage shows, televised performances and motion pictures. Steve's compositions and arrangements have been published and recorded since 1969. Originally from Humboldt, Tennessee Mr. Nichols grew up in Miami, Florida from age seven, later spending more than thirty years outside the mainland U.S.A.. He now resides in Ft. McCoy, Florida.

title: Violet Dreams
extra:
Hello my name is Kelvin Coles
Singer/Songwriter from Baltimore,Maryland.
I have been involved with musical projects since the age of 10. I have played Trombone, Trumpet, and Baritone Horn in Concert and Stage Bands. The first instrument I learned to play was the Coronet Horn.

There was a time during the 80's- 90's when Live Bands were thriving here in Baltimore, Maryland. I played Funk/R&B here in Baltimore during that time, it was a lot of fun and I learned a lot from those around me.
There were so many groups and acts from Baltimore that produced many Stars during the time I played that still today have an influence on my music.


My natural gift of music comes from my father Melvin Coles who was a touring Guitar player during the 1950's. He played along side many other artist during his tour in Europe.

Later I honed my skills into writing songs for groups.People in my area started asking me for songs so I was obliged just to hear them sing it ;-)

Former Song Of The Year 2006 Honorable Mention http://www.songoftheyear.com/winners/2006/runnerups/nov/novhon.htm.


"Music Is The Universal Language Of The World "



Thank you for stopping by and listening.
Remember ..
" If you light someone's candle it will also brighten your path as well "

Unvictorian Victoria
extra: More of a "ditty" than a song. It was inspired by an article in a newspaper which revealed that a portrait of Queen Victoria, naked from waist-up, had been found in Windsor Castle. I had always thought of her as, well Victorian, and was surprised by the article (needless to say it appeared in a Murdoch "rag", so it could well be untrue. I decided to write a song based on Prince Albert's response to the Queen's shenanigans. From the Self Tort debut CD "N.I.C"

title: City Of Hate
extra:
Why not leave promising careers to chase a dream in New York City? You only live once and even then for a relatively short period of time.

In the beginning there were three men in Lexington, KY. These men were Cedric Sparkman, Laurence Adams and Jason Matuskiewicz.

Really, though, this band started at one discrete moment in time. In Hazard, Perry County, Kentucky, the foothills of Appalachia, when Cedric saw Laurence buy a copy of The Smithsâ Hatful of Hollow at the local Wal-mart and thought, âHey, that boy who could barely play âHey Judeâ might be pretty cool after all.â So, as young, foolish musical men are so often wont to do, they decided to start a cover bandâa mixture of The Smiths and David Bowie covers. Yes, in Hazard, Kentucky. I know, right?

They carried this back to the teaming metropolis of Lexington, KY, where both were then living. In the meantime, Laurence met Jason, who was then but one modest young man playing acoustic singer-songwriter shows somewhat haphazardlyâwith little ambition and even less effort. After sometime in Morehead, Kentucky, the hardwood capital of the world, and Heidelberg, Germany, Cedric returned to Lexington, and he and Laurence succeeded in putting together a Smiths cover band that didnât actually play Smiths songs, called Varsoviaâwhich is to say it comprised equal parts pastiche and encomium. They invited Jason to join the band, but with the catch that he play bass, an instrument he had never played before. It turned out Jason was a natural. And Varsovia released two E.P.sâbrilliantly titled EP1 and EP2âbefore calling it a day in 2009.

In the interest of making everything as difficult as possible, which, along with arguing like brothers, is a favorite Candidate pastime, after deciding to form a new band, Cedric, Jason and Laurence wrote over 30 new songs before playing a show. After a couple shows, the band recorded an album, A New Life. Although the songs were all written collaboratively, the album contained a loose narrative roughly following the dissolution of Jasonâs marriage. The released the album in June 2011. The album was received well, but tragedy befell the band and robbed the band of its momentum.

Meanwhile, over the course of his time in the band, Cedric Sparkman succumbed to that emotion that is the inveterate enemy of rock n roll, love. When his girlfriendâwho is wonderful, by the wayâgraduated from her MFA program in New York City, she and Cedric decided they would live there. And so he did in August 2011. Jason, deciding there was little to keep them at his lucrative career as a young lawyer, other than money, comfort and the promise of being able to buy food in the future, and Laurence, wishing to test his mettle in the Brooklyn wastes, they would join Cedricâchasing a dream in the big city.

Shortly after arriving in New York, Candidate met Chris Infusino, a real live pro drummer, who joined them for their first show in NYC. He killed it. After the show, Jason asked Chris if he would like to join them in recording the bandâs next album. Chris asked when this recording was to begin, to which Jaosn replied, âNext week.â Ah, Candidate, always keeping everything as difficult as possible. Chris cleared his schedule and joined the band.

Teaming up with boy genius and super producer, Justin Craig, the band created their second albumâa sonically expansive, forward looking record. The album continues and concludes the narrative that started on the first LP, âA New Life.â This time, however, the narrative was shaped by Cedric, although the narrator is the same mostly fictional character. The album reflects the personal struggles and ultimate triumph he experienced upon his move to New York.

Candidate is currently seeking a label to partner with in putting out the album.

title: Goodman Chic
extra:
DaMar Marcus-Lee Fairbanks also known by rapper name Balenciaga Banks, is an American Recording Artist and Fashion Designer for Perry Ellis International. The rapper, stylist, artist holds 2 Associate of Arts degrees in Fashion Design and Fashion Merchandising. Known for his work ethic the full-time fashion designer and musician has released 6 mixtapes in the span 22 months. Creating all the artwork for each mixtape front and back covers. Balenciaga Banks is a rare American talent that is building a legacy in the entertainment and fashion Industries at the same time.

MUSIC: His first mixtape titled âThe Kat_Walk was released January 30, 2010 for online listen only. The mixtape has a mellow ear chalked full of fashion terminology. The smooth flowing mixtape over melodic beats prove to be good, yet different introduction. âThe Dapper Wears Monacoâ was released exactly 6 months later and was available for online listen and free hard copy hand out. This mixtape had great reviews as the designer/rapper did a remake of the movie âThe Devil Wears Pradaâ in hip-hop music form. The mixtape had excerpts from the movie at the beginning of each track, building a plot for what the song was about. January 4th 2011 marked the release of a 3rd mixtape by Balenciaga Banks titled âThe Heartbeat of Americaâ this mixtape drew critical acclaim. The rapper changed gears and left the F (fashion) OUT! Dedicated to his home state of Ohio. Balenciaga Banks online release saw huge numbers and downloads mainly by the newly acquired Ohio listeners who he longed to please. Just two months later the 4th mixtape dropped "The Kat_Walk 2: Cambridge-vs-Oxford". In an effort to build on the success of the previous mixtape a huge online initiative was the approach to back the new music. The rapper ran into a roadblock as the quickly released mixtape lacked the buzz that the previous projects provided and didnât do well via online listens. Four months later Balenciaga Banks dust off the microphone and released his 5th mixtape âCaviar and Cigarettesâ. The mixtape was a online only release and proved a successful comeback for the discouraged artist. Billed, as âEmotional-Rapâ Balenciaga Banks seemed to make himself vulnerable on the whole project. The first track âTwo Câsâ talked about his Cincinnati up bringing, grade school and fashion industry success. The listeners who wrote him off were back and gain a new respect for the Cincinnati, Ohio musician. Balenciaga Banks released his 6th mixtape âBlue Blood Chicâ December 15, 2011 available via online listen.
http://soundcloud.com/caviarandcigarettes/sets/blue-blood-chic

FASHION: Balenciaga Banks is working full-time for Perry Ellis International as a menswear designer. Prior to that, he was a menswear design intern for iconic fashion brand Club Monaco a division of Polo Ralph Lauren.

AWARDS: Balenciaga Banks earned Funkshion Miami Fashion Week âMenswear Designer of the Year 2009â heâs also featured in the CFDAâs Emerging Fashion Designers Book published October 23, 2010

title: Eskimos
extra: Eskimos (or Esquimaux) or InuitâYupik (for Alaska: InupiatâYupik) peoples are indigenous peoples who have traditionally inhabited the circumpolar region from eastern Siberia (Russia), across Alaska (United States), Canada, and Greenland.

Twenty-two is an even composite number, its proper divisors being 1, 2 and 11. 22 is the sixth discrete semiprime and the fourth in the (2.q) family. With 21 it forms the second discrete semiprime pair. 22 has an aliquot sum of 14 and is the fifth composite number found in the 7-aliquot tree. It has a 7- member aliquot sequence 22, 14, 10, 8, 7, 1, 0 of which the next two members are themselves discrete semiprimes, 22 is the first discrete semiprime exhibiting this property. 169 also has 14 as its aliquot sum. 22 is itself the aliquot sum of two numbers 20, 38.
Twenty-two is a pentagonal number and a centered heptagonal number. When cutting a circle with just six line segments, the maximum number of pieces that can be so created is 22,[1] thus 22 is a central polygonal number (see lazy caterer's sequence).
The sum of the totient function for the first eight integers is 22. 22 is a Perrin number, preceded in the sequence by 10, 12, 17.
22 divided by 7 approximates the irrational number ?, the ratio of the circumference of a circle to its diameter.
Since it is possible to find sequences of 22 consecutive integers such that each inner member shares a factor with either the first or the last member, 22 is an Erd?sâWoods number.
It is a Smith number in base 10.
[edit]In physics and chemistry

The atomic number of titanium is 22.
[edit]In religion

There are 22 letters in the Hebrew alphabet
There are 22 chapters of the Revelation of John in the Bible
In the Kabbalah, there are 22 paths between the sephiroth
Psalm 22 (22nd in the Book of Psalm in the King James Bible), described by the New American Standard Bible as the "A Cry of Anguish and a Song of Praise", is the Psalm to which the crucified and dying Jesus makes reference, citing its first verse in Aramaic (Matthew 27:46; Mark 15:34)
There are 22 verses in Surah "Al Burooj"(The Zodiac, or Constellations), in the Quran. Linking the Zodiac and the mystery of the number 22, as found in the Major Arcana.
[edit]In numerals

In the divinatory tarot, there are 22 major arcana cards. These cards are numbered 0-21, so it is a matter of interpretation whether The Fool or The World is card number 22. The latter card is almost always associated with hard workers, a red-gold colour, and a rose-gold gemstone. The digital root of the 22 is the 4, which is the number of hard work.
[edit]In sports

In rugby union:
The "22" is a the line in each half of the field which is 22 metres from the respective try line. It has significance in a number of laws particularly relating to kicking the ball away.
In all international matches and almost all top-level league competitions, each team is allowed to name a squad of 22 players for a given match.
In Australian rules football, each team is allowed a squad of 22 players (18 on the field and 4 interchanges).
22 is the number of players on the field in a football (soccer) match, and also the number of players on the field at any one time in an American football match.
The jersey number 22 has been retired by several North American sports teams in honor of past playing greats:
In Major League Baseball:
The Baltimore Orioles, for Hall of Famer Jim Palmer.
In the NBA:
The Boston Celtics, for Hall of Famer Ed Macauley.
The Cleveland Cavaliers, for Larry Nance.
The Dallas Mavericks, for Rolando Blackman.
The Houston Rockets and Portland Trail Blazers, both for Hall of Famer Clyde Drexler.
The Los Angeles Lakers, for Hall of Famer Elgin Baylor.
The Lakers have separately honored #22 for Hall of Famer Slater Martin, who wore the number before Baylor when the team was the Minneapolis Lakers.
The New York Knicks, for Hall of Famer Dave DeBusschere.
In the NFL:
The Baltimore Colts retired #22 for Buddy Young. Since the team's controversial relocation to Indianapolis, the current Indianapolis Colts have not retired any numbers, but continue to honor all numbers retired by the franchise in Baltimore.
The Detroit Lions, for Hall of Famer Bobby Layne.
The New Orleans Saints, for Tracy Porter.
The Dallas Cowboys have a policy of not retiring numbers. However, the team has not issued #22 since Hall of Famer Emmitt Smith left the team in 2002.
In the NHL:
The New York Islanders, for Hall of Famer Mike Bossy.
The length of a cricket pitch is 22 yards.
"22" is a common name for the .22 calibre .22 Long Rifle cartridge.
"22" is the number of cars in NASCAR's Sprint Cup Series and Nationwide Series, both Dodges currently owned by Penske Racing. A. J. Allmendinger has the Sprint Cup ride in 2012, and the Nationwide car is driven by Brad Keselowski with Jacques Villeneuve taking over for road courses.
"22" was the number of Lewis Hamilton's McLaren-Mercedes in 2008 and is the number of Jenson Button's Brawn-Mercedes in 2009, both winning the drivers' championship that year.
"22" was the jersey number of Mark Ingram, running back for the University of Alabama, who was the Crimson Tide's first ever Heisman Trophy winner. He did so in 2009, the same year the Tide won their 22nd SEC championship.
[edit]In music

The name of a song by punk band Millencolin.
In Jay-Z's song "22 Two's", he rhymes the words: too, to and two, 22 times in the first verse.
Iron Maiden has a song named "22 Acacia Avenue".
Death Metal band Hypocrisy album "Catch 22" released in year 2002.
Lily Allen has a song titled "22" from her album It's Not Me, It's You.
Paul Weller has a song and album named 22 Dreams. The album contains 22 songs on it, including the song "22 Dreams".
The Norwegian electronica project Ugress uses 22 as a recurring theme. All four albums features a track with 22 in the title.
Australian alternative rock band Sick Puppies have a song called Catch 22 on the album Dog's Breakfast.
[edit]In journalism, literature, fashion, art, film and television

Catch-22, the 1961 novel (and its 1970 film version) by Joseph Heller, which consequently gave rise to the expression "catch-22"
Twenty-Two, Season 2âepisode 17 (February 10, 1961) of the 1959-64 TV series The Twilight Zone in which a hospitalized dancer has nightmares about a sinister nurse inviting her to Room 22, the hospital morgue.
In the online series Prom Queen, the number 22 factors prominently into the story, appearing in numerous episodes, and the digits in the date of the prom (6/9/07) add up to 22.
Revista 22, a magazine published in Romania
The typical (minimum) number of episodes in a season for a television program broadcast on a major American network is 22.
Insult comedian Jack E. Leonard, on his numerous television game show appearances, answered with "22" to any question requiring a numerical response.
On the show Most Evil, a forensic psychiatrist scales from 1 to 22, evilness is mentally evaluated.
There are 22 stars in the Paramount Films logo.
The typical length of a half hour sitcom not including commercials is 22 minutes.
In the 1942 film Casablanca, Rick's CafÃ© Americain has a trick roulette wheel. Rick (played by Humphrey Bogart) uncharacteristically takes pity on a young Bulgarian refugee couple. The husband has lost most of his money at roulette, trying to win enough to bribe police captain Renault. Rick suggests the man bet on 22. After the number comes up, Rick tells him to let it all ride. He does, and wins again. Rick tells him to cash in his winnings ... and never come back.
[edit]In weights and measures

The number of yards in a chain.
A cricket pitch is 22 yards in length
[edit]In computing

The standard port number for the Secure Shell protocol
A quotation mark (in a URL it appears as a "%22")
[edit]In technology

22 is the designation of the USAF stealth fighter, the F-22 Raptor.
.22 Long Rifle
[edit]In photography

f/22 is the largest f-stop (and thus smallest aperture) available on most lenses made for single-lens reflex cameras
[edit]In politics

The central number in the numerologically-based political platform of fringe U.S. Presidential candidate Love 22
22nd Bahman 1357 (according to the Iranian calendar; February 11, 1979) a revolution took place in Iran resulting in the decline of Pahlavi Dynasty in Iran which consequently led to establishment of the Islamic Republic of Iran under the leadership of Ruh-o llah Khomayni. Latter this day has been annually celebrated by the Iranian government.
[edit]In jargon

In French, "22" is used as a phrase to warn of the coming of the police (typically "22, v'lÃ  les flics !", "22, here come the cops!")
[edit]In other fields

Twenty-two may also refer to:
The number of the French department CÃ´tes-d'Armor
The Titanic was traveling at a speed of 22 knots before it crashed into an iceberg.
In bingo, 22 is referred to as 'Two Little Ducks'
The license plate number of Edirne, Turkey

title: Frozen
extra:
DaMar Marcus-Lee Fairbanks also known by rapper name Balenciaga Banks, is an American Recording Artist and Fashion Designer for Perry Ellis International. The rapper, stylist, artist holds 2 Associate of Arts degrees in Fashion Design and Fashion Merchandising. Known for his work ethic the full-time fashion designer and musician has released 6 mixtapes in the span 22 months. Creating all the artwork for each mixtape front and back covers. Balenciaga Banks is a rare American talent that is building a legacy in the entertainment and fashion Industries at the same time.

MUSIC: His first mixtape titled âThe Kat_Walk was released January 30, 2010 for online listen only. The mixtape has a mellow ear chalked full of fashion terminology. The smooth flowing mixtape over melodic beats prove to be good, yet different introduction. âThe Dapper Wears Monacoâ was released exactly 6 months later and was available for online listen and free hard copy hand out. This mixtape had great reviews as the designer/rapper did a remake of the movie âThe Devil Wears Pradaâ in hip-hop music form. The mixtape had excerpts from the movie at the beginning of each track, building a plot for what the song was about. January 4th 2011 marked the release of a 3rd mixtape by Balenciaga Banks titled âThe Heartbeat of Americaâ this mixtape drew critical acclaim. The rapper changed gears and left the F (fashion) OUT! Dedicated to his home state of Ohio. Balenciaga Banks online release saw huge numbers and downloads mainly by the newly acquired Ohio listeners who he longed to please. Just two months later the 4th mixtape dropped "The Kat_Walk 2: Cambridge-vs-Oxford". In an effort to build on the success of the previous mixtape a huge online initiative was the approach to back the new music. The rapper ran into a roadblock as the quickly released mixtape lacked the buzz that the previous projects provided and didnât do well via online listens. Four months later Balenciaga Banks dust off the microphone and released his 5th mixtape âCaviar and Cigarettesâ. The mixtape was a online only release and proved a successful comeback for the discouraged artist. Billed, as âEmotional-Rapâ Balenciaga Banks seemed to make himself vulnerable on the whole project. The first track âTwo Câsâ talked about his Cincinnati up bringing, grade school and fashion industry success. The listeners who wrote him off were back and gain a new respect for the Cincinnati, Ohio musician. Balenciaga Banks released his 6th mixtape âBlue Blood Chicâ December 15, 2011 available via online listen.
http://soundcloud.com/caviarandcigarettes/sets/blue-blood-chic

FASHION: Balenciaga Banks is working full-time for Perry Ellis International as a menswear designer. Prior to that, he was a menswear design intern for iconic fashion brand Club Monaco a division of Polo Ralph Lauren.

AWARDS: Balenciaga Banks earned Funkshion Miami Fashion Week âMenswear Designer of the Year 2009â heâs also featured in the CFDAâs Emerging Fashion Designers Book published October 23, 2010

extra:
Luiza Staniec has been playing the piano, singing and composing forever.

âI come from a small village tucked away in eastern Poland. Iâd always dreamed of going far, far away from there, exploring the world, performing my music, composing my songs and meeting different people. Music is my first language and my best friend. Since I found that piano at the community centre in my village when I was 6 years old, I knew what I was going to do for the rest of my life and which direction I was heading:
Music is my passion and my life.â

After finishing at the Music School Of Singers in Poznan, Luiza was a frequent performer on the Lublin music scene where she fronted the all-female band Matka (Mother) as the lead vocalist, pianist and composer. She also gave airtime to up-and-coming artists as a radio presenter for Akademickie Radio âCentrumâ (Student Radio âCentreâ) where she had her own show, Your Demo.

Soon she became a missionary of sorts, travelling the world with her musical message. Her âmissionâ took her to Japan where she lived for two years.

In 2004-2005 Luiza, together with Matka, collaborated with Micha? Wisniewski, a singer of great renown in Poland, on his project Red Head. Luiza still enjoys a considerable amount of success working alongside some of the best known Polish artists as a composer and lyricist. Her credits include one of Ewelina Flinta's best loved songs, Zaluje (I Regret).

In 2005 Luiza joined Telewizor, a Polish alternative rock band, to produce the album Sowy I Cmy (Owls and Moths) which enjoyed great critical acclaim from the music press. This album opened the doors to some well known TV shows, one hosted by the hugely popular Kuba Wojewodzki. The song Plyne, Gine (Swimming, Drowning) was used in the TV movie Magda M which attracted a large audience. Her composition âSowy I Cmyâ ("Owls and Moths") found favour with the producers of another movie, Wieza (The Tower).

In September 2007, Luiza was a finalist in the prestigious Vena International Music Festival in Poland , sponsored by Pepsi. Her song Where Have You Been reached third place, having been immensely popular with the audience and judges.

In October 2007, Luiza released the album Ja To Ja (I Am Me), with eleven original tracks, all composed and arranged in Luizaâs own inviting style. This very feminine album exudes the warmth of Luiza's voice and the tranquility of her piano playing. The music on the album represents a unique life journey, with its many wonders and turns. Just like most of Luiza's songs, the material on Ja To Ja is as heartfelt and personal as an album can get.

Luiza, has been living in the North East of Scotland for more than three years, performing and composing.

She just recorded her five new songs with Grammy nominated producers Andy Bradfield and Avril Mackintosh, who have recorded with world famous artists such as Everything But the Girl, Tori Amos, Alanis Morissette and Tom Jones.

I decided to become an artist at age 13 and started doing talent shows. My grandfather was an aspiring musician and died to make his dream come true, and I plan on doing the same. extra: Paul Venable was born and raised in a small town in Southeast New Mexico but currently lives in New York City. His life as a vocalist began after winning a church sponsored singing contest that included New Mexico and West Texas. "I've pretty much been singing for anyone who will listen ever since" says Paul. It was during his college years that Paul got the songwriting bug, and shortly after receiving his diploma with a minor in Music, he moved to Nashville, TN. Paul spent almost 10 years in Nashville where he says: "I had the great opportunity to meet some lifelong friends and play and write with some fantastic musicians. title: House Of Three
extra:
"This was the kind of music that I had always wanted to write," says Jim Ivins about his Spring 2011 release "Late Night Drive." After spending three and a half years fronting rising Richmond, VA pop rock band, The Jim Ivins Band, Ivins decided to take a step back and strip down his sound. Drawing influence from artists like Jon Foreman, Sufjan Stevens, and Ryan Adams, "Late Night Drive" sees Ivins take the leap into "mature" artist territory.

While love has always been the cornerstone of Ivins' lyrical story, his new EP sees him step his lyrical game up, touching on a more diverse set of topics, from self-reflection ("Late Night Drive"), to fear of the unknown ("Riptides"), to the tragic 2010 death of his mother ("House of Three"). "I feel like when you make the songs this raw and intimate, it lends itself to making the lyrical content more personal, and that's exactly what's happened here," Ivins relates.

Setting out to create a songbook that's perfect for winter and driving in the dark, Ivins was ecstatic to finally have the material to contribute to a sound that's such a huge part of his musical self.

After releasing his solo debut "99Â¢ Dreams" on his own in September 2007, opening for Mae as his debut performance and CD release, Ivins formed The Jim Ivins Band with his brother Jack (drums), and friends Bobby Gary (bass), and Drew Martin (guitar). Ever since, the band have been making a name for themselves, securing a licensing deal with MTV, touring the east coast, showcasing at the 2009 Miami Music Festival, and opening for artists like Carolina Liar, The Rocket Summer, Parachute, and Carbon Leaf, among others, all while charming audiences young and old with their Goo Goo Dolls-influenced brand of acoustic pop rock. Their tunes even caught the ear of Jim's idol, Ace Enders (The Early November), who would go on to produce two tracks on their 2009 self-titled EP.

title: Nicht zu spÃ¤t (Not to late)
extra:
The idea to this song i found by chating with a friend of mine on the myownmusic portal, Dino Cuoco!
We talked about his songs and that he likes doing songs with vocoder and
found out that i have no song yet with vocoder vocals!
After that chat on pure coincidence i found the vocoder i used for the start of the song!
Cause i like that vocoder very much the base of the song was ready!
The rest of the vocals i found cause of the character of the instumental i worked on at that time!
And so one coincidence followed the other,
for example the ideas for the rest of the text i found in my It project i work on!
A little bit of cyborg vocals as special character for the song and
some cool lyrics from my daugther who gives the break a special note!
After all my new song is out now, hope you enjoy!

Wenn's mal wieder etwas lÃ¤nger dauert!
Das Instrumental zum Song war recht schnell fertig!
Doch dann kamen die Vocals!
Bei einem Chat mit Dino Cuoco (Voco-Dino:-) entstand die Idee,
einen Song mit Vocoder zu erstellen,
da ein solcher in meiner Sammlung bis dato noch fehlt!
Ãber den Vocoder vom Anfang bin ich durch Zufall gestolpert!
Irgendwie hat der mir so gut gefallen,
das er rein muÃte!
Am Anfang war er mitten im Song,
was meinen beiden Ladies (meine Frau sowie meine Tochter)
unabhÃ¤ngig voneinander mit passt nicht zum Song ablehnten!
Und wenn beide Ladies nein sagen,
dann ist nichts zu machen!
Also ging die Suche und das umbauen los!
Eine Grund-Vorstellung hatte ich,
die auch recht schnell fertig war,
aber irgendwie fehlte noch was!
Bei den fehlenden Parts,
wurde ich mal wieder im Projekt-Geschehen meines
noch immer laufenden IT-Projektes fÃ¼ndig!
Zum SchluÃ stand dann noch ein Part fÃ¼r Jill auf der Liste,
diesen habe ich auch wieder durch Zufall beim stÃ¶bern im Internet gefunden!
Jill hat einen abgewandelten Text von Konfuzius,
welcher dem Break, eine ganz individuelle Note verleiht!
Und somit ist der Song letzenendes dann doch noch,
nach etwas lÃ¤ngerer Zeit als eigentlich gedacht fertig geworden!
Aber so ist es wohl mit manchen Songs!
Manchmal passt es direkt und
manchmal braucht es ein wenig mehr Zeit!
WÃ¼nsche viel Spass beim reinhÃ¶ren und
hoffe, das alles soweit passt!
Bin fÃ¼r Anregungen und Kritik wie immer offen!

title: Schwerelos(Weightless)
extra:
The idea to this song i found in the salt-pool in the fÃ¼rthermare a leasure pool in nuremberg. By floating in the water i thought i could write a song about the fealing to be weightless! The result of this idea is now this song!
Instrumentation:
Gladiator, ElektraX, Alchemy Sampleplayer,Z3TA+ 2 and some samples from the magix soundpool
Der Songtext ist dem Sole-Becken,
im FÃ¼rthermare bei NÃ¼rnberg zu verdanken!
Da man hier wirklich wie schwerelos auf dem Wasser liegt und
von Unterwasserlautsprechern mit Chillout-KlÃ¤ngen berieselt wird,
kam mir die Idee einen Song zum Thema Schwerelosigkeit zu machen!
Und so hat sich von Badebesuch zu Badebesuch immer mehr Text hinzugesellt und das Ergebnis des ganzen ist nun hier zu hÃ¶ren!
Hoffe der Song und das Mastering passt soweit!
Kommentar und VerbesserungsvorschlÃ¤ge sind wie immer willkommen!

Gladiator, ElektraX, Alchemy Sampleplayer,Z3TA+ 2 sowie ein paar Samples aus dem Magix Soundpool

album: He Took My Name To The Cross
title: 9:16 AM
extra:
Where will I be when the Lord comes?

Indie Nashville Songwriter / Recording Artist and Morro Bay California Worship Leader Chris Keith has 3 Cd's and is coming out with his long awaited 4th CD to be released October 1, 2012.

Hits songs off his 1st. Cd "He Took My Name To The Cross" are: "Daddy Dance with Me" A popular Daddy Daughter wedding dance song played at wedding's across the country, the new "Butterfly Kisses" or "Cinderella". Written for his daughter Tayler when she was 3 years old, she pulled on his shirt saying "Daddy dance with me" A song was born. Also title song "He Took My Name To the Cross" Played at Easter in churches, homes, and ipods across the country. The most inspired Easter song in this decade!

The 2nd Cd "Walkin'" has hit songs "I'm Afraid" written after Chris' son Jesse had 4 needless brain surgeries, because his wife Shelene was not given a simple $25 GBS test at 35 weeks of pregnancy. Chris and his family changed the law nationally. Now, every pregnant woman in the US is tested for GBS. Also on the "Walkin' Cd is the "Sexy God song "Song of Songs" Chris wrote for Shelene on Valentine's Day.

The 3rd Cd "Knockin'" has hit songs "Mary's Baby" Played at churches and homes across America, it is he new "Mary did you know" song. And the touching 9/11 song "In America" shows that God still lives, and our flag still flies "In America". Like many fans across America; you will love and play Chris' Cd's over and over. Up lifting and Inspirational!

album: He Took My Name To The Cross
title: Im Here - Bag Pipes on the Bluff!
extra:
You will love this song "I'm Here" (Bag Pipes) Written on the Central Coast of California in a little beautiful town called Cambria. Chris and his family were on the beach, as the fog was starting to roll in and the waves were crashing against the rocks. He was watching his little kids play in the sand, and he looked at his wife and said "It can't get any more perfect then this" Then all of the sudden, off in the distance on the bluff near by they hear the sound of Bag pipes. He looked back at his wife and shrugged his shoulders and said "I was wrong-it Can...God is Great!"

title: Dopeboy city2
extra:
"D'ANDRE KASAAN WAASHINGTON AKA PRODUXK"

I WAS BORN IN CHARLESTON SC MAY 18 1977 .IM 33 YRS OF AGE , MUSIC HAS ALWAYS HAD AN INFLUENCE ON ME I'VE BEEN WRITTING AND PERFORMING AT AN EARLY AGE.

IVE BEEN INSPIRED BY A FEW GREAT ARTISTES SUCH AS,ERICK B AND RAHKIM LL COOL J, RUSSELL SIMMONS AND MANY OTHERS. IN 1994 IN ATLANTA GA I DISPLAYED MY TALENT THAT LANDED ME A SPOT AT THE AFRICAN ARTS FEST. AND THE SWEET AUBURNE FEST. WERE I PERFORMED ALONG SIDE DJ. LIL JOHN AN THE GHETTO ALLSTARS

WHICH GOT ME RECONIZED BY AN ENTERTAIMENT COMPANY CALLED COFFEE ENT. WERE I STAY FOR TWO YRS. AN DEVELOPED MY UNCANNY SKILLS PERFORMING AN OPENIN SHOWS AT THE CAT FISH STATION BAR AN GRILL ON PONCE DEL LEON ATL. GA ALSO STARBREAKERS WITH JERRY KING WHEN I WAS WITH A RAP GROUP BY THE NAME OF PRIMEFACTOR.I CONTRIBUTED MY TIME AN HARDWORK INTO THE ARTIST I CLAIM TO BE PRODUXK. LATER ON I MET LISA LOPES WERE AS SHE WAS MY GOOD FRIEND AN MENTOR AN HOW SHE SHOWED ME THAT MY WRITTING SKILL AAND EAR TO MAKE A HIT OVERWHELMED ME TO SUCCEED AN KEEP PUSHING.1995 WOODSTOCK GA IN THE STUDIO LEARNING THE ROPES FROM MC BREED AN JAZZY FAYE ON BEING A ARTIST AN TO RITE FROM THE HEART.1996 ATL OLYMPICS OPENING PERFOMANCE AT OLYMPIC PARK ATL.ALSO IN THAT SAME YRS CLUB PARADOX MARIETTA GA HEADLINE FOR A STARBREAKER EVENT BROADCAST ON PBS WHICH GOT ME AN INTERVIEW WITH A MAJOR LABEL IVE ALSO WORKED WITH TERRANCE ALGUR WHO PRODUCED A HIT SINGLE FOR QUESTION MARK ASYLIUM. MY LIST OF PEOPLE IS NOT MY CREDENTIALS BUT THE INFLUCE I HAVE IN STILL IN MY MAKES ME THE ARTIST I AM.

extra:
www.ChrisKeith.com
Selected on Music XRay for Hottest New Artist Finalist for 2013!
ww.ChrisKeith.com
Indie Nashville Songwriter / Singer Recording Artist and Morro Bay California Worship Leader released his 4th CD "Churchman" in the fall of 2012. Chris with his Nashville team are working on backgrounds for TV and film.

Hits songs off his 1st. Cd "He Took My Name To The Cross" are: "Daddy Dance with Me" A popular Daddy Daughter wedding dance song played at wedding's across the country, the new "Butterfly Kisses" or "Cinderella". Written for his daughter Tayler when she was 3 years old, she pulled on his shirt saying "Daddy dance with me" A song was born. Also title song "He Took My Name To the Cross" Played at Easter in churches, and homes, across the country. The most inspired Easter song in this decade!

The 2nd Cd "Walkin'" has hit songs "I'm Afraid" written after Chris' son Jesse had 4 needless brain surgeries, because his wife Shelene was not given a simple $25 GBS test at 35 weeks of pregnancy. Chris and his family changed the law nationally. Now, every pregnant woman in the US is tested for GBS. Also on the "Walkin' Cd is the "Sexy God song "Song of Songs" Chris wrote for Shelene on Valentine's Day.

The 3rd Cd "Knockin'" has hit songs "Mary's Baby" Played at churches and homes across America, it is he new "Mary did you know" song. And the touching 9/11 song "In America" shows that God still lives, and our flag still flies "In America". Like many fans across America; you will love and play Chris' Cd's over and over. Up lifting and Inspirational!

title: Yes, I figure it out
extra:
I write pop, dance/electronia and R&B songs. I like to blend new style into my music and try various kinds of arrangement.

I have only started to produce music for about a year, but my songs have catchy melodies, fun rhythmic beats and great originality.

Currently I don't live in the US ( I am living in China). I am hoping that I can have a job at a US record label as a songwriter, music arranger, and back ground singer. Still, my best hope is to get a record deal.

My future plan is to go to US next year, and play live show and sell CD myself. Still, I am improving my production skills and vocal skills and all other kinds of music skills.

title: Precious Jesus - Children Singing, Great for Kids Performance, Church, Inspirational!
extra:
You will love this sweet song. Chris' wife Christine died of Cancer, and before she died she wrote "Precious Jesus". Chris held on to this song looking for the perfect voice. One day he looked down at his sweet 7 year old daughter Tayler and knew it was her voice he was waiting for all these years. A sweet beautiful song with Tayler's sweet beautiful voice! (Great for church children's choirs)
Just back from Nashville "Hot off the press" is Chris Keith's long awaited 4th CD "Churchman". Blues to Rock to a Chill, Jazz feel..Enjoy!

Chris Keith composes with his Nashville team. He has been working with this team for over 10 years. They are concentrating on thematic projects for TV and film.

Indie Nashville Songwriter / Recording Artist and Morro Bay California Worship Leader Chris Keith has 4 Cd's.
Hits songs off his 1st. Cd "He Took My Name To The Cross" are "Daddy Dance with Me" A popular Daddy Daughter wedding dance song played at wedding's across the country, the new "Butterfly Kisses" or "Cinderella". Written for his daughter Tayler when she was 3 years old, she pulled on his shirt saying "Daddy dance with me" A song was born. Also title song "He Took My Name To the Cross" The most inspired Easter song in this decade!

The 2nd Cd "Walkin'" has hit songs "I'm Afraid" written after Chris' son Jesse had 4 needless brain surgeries, because his wife Shelene was not given a simple $25 GBS test at 35 weeks of pregnancy. Chris and his family changed the law nationally. Now, every pregnant woman in the US is tested for GBS. www.theJesseCause.org
Also on the "Walkin' Cd is the "Sexy God song "Song of Songs" Chris wrote for Shelene on Valentine's Day.

The 3rd Cd "Knockin'" has hit songs "Mary's Baby" Played at churches and homes across America, it is the new "Mary did you know". And the touching 9/11 song "In America" shows that God still lives, and our flag still flies "In America". Like many fans across America; you will love and play Chris' Cd's over and over. Up lifting and Inspirational!

extra:
Listening to The Como Brothers music you can hear their love of the blues, pop music, and rock n' roll.

Matt and Andrew Como are singers, songwriters, and performers. Their new album Imagination was recorded with Grammy Award winning producer Graham Marsh (Bruno Mars, CeeLo Green) at Germano Studios in NYC. Playing with Matt and Andrew on the record is Grammy winning artist and king of groove Steve Jordan on drums. Steve is popularly known the beat behind the Mark Ronson/Bruno Mars song "Uptown Funk" and a member of John Mayer Trio. Also playing on the record is renowned John Mayer/Rufus Wainwright keyboardist Andy Burton. The album is available for pre-order on iTunes now and will be officially released on August 10th, 2015!

The Como Brothers have also been known to work with with acclaimed drummer Aaron Sterling known for his drumming on Taylor Swift's RED album, and Sara Bareilles' music including the song "Brave". Aaron and Andy Burton recently played at The Como Brothers "Imagination" album pre-release show in NY.

The Como Brothers discography:

"Imagination" EP (August, 2015)
âBaby Stepsâ Album (October, 2013)
âStill Watersâ EP (March, 2013)
"The Speed of Sound" EP (January, 2012)
Their music has been on Keeping up with the Kardashians, MTV's Real World and Oxygen Channel's Best Ink. Indie Movie Wingman and in a Canon Trade Show Commercial.

http://www.imdb.me/comobrothersband

Having grown up performing in a Beatles tribute band with their Dad and Uncle on Long Island The Como Brothers are no strangers to the music scene. Matt and Andrew grew up with music from an early age and have been honing their craft as established singer/songwriters and performers for years in venues across the East Coast of the US.

title: Cafrodeep & Tshepi - Pick Me Up (Deep Sixty Lazy Instrumental Mix) - CCT001-web-2011
extra: From the core hearts of South Africa, Soweto two fromer High school friend come together to bring you one of S.A's finest E.P. Pick me up is a Song which was lyricaly written by Tshepiso Dikgole, describing a certain situation at a certain place and time, she brings the situation to life with her beautiful voice and talent. This track has moved the hearts and minds of many and is yet to move even more.. with the exceptional production of cafrodeep and the superb vocals of Tshepi combined to make this outstanding HIT!!! Tshepi is an up and coming Vocalist from Soweto who has much to offer the music industry of S.A she is still a sparkling talent at the her Dawns with a whole lot to offer... Cafrodeep is the producer of the song, and has been around in the underground scene for quiet some time now. He has the heart of a perfectionist and works hard to create quality music for the masses... and him and his Label 'Citynoiz Entertainment' have alot to offer the world of music so keep a really close eye on him... THE REMIXERS Thabiso aka Deep Sixty is a 21 year old DJ, producer and founder of GrooveMoove Recordings. He has a unique mild but groovy ryhthm... A style that is only true to him and is well known for his Deepness. He is truely one Producer to be respected with his humbleness talent and proffesionalism. Deep Sixty's GrooveMoove Recordings are set to rock the global house music scene. So keep a really close eye on Him Smami is one talented Producer from the heart of S.A [Soweto] and he has his major flavour of Style when it comes to deep house. He is extremely talented and is one of the Cacooning talents of S.A... his talent is not to be missed it just speaks for itself... Last but not least DJ Sibz a fast growing name in S.A for his diversity and creativity. his work is outstanding and his remixes are amazing... He has worked with many artists both up and coming and well known. His music catches you by surpirse and will leave you always asking for more and more... For more inforamtion: facebook.com/cafrodeep.citynoiz twitter.com/cafrodeep myspace.com/djcafro soundcloud.com/cafrodeep

extra:
I'm19 years old,but I feel older,been thru so much stuff in my life,my only escape is to writ support local and underground music with everything I am. I been doing this music thing since I was a wee young lad. read my bio and you'll get what I mean. Writing music and making beats is the only thing I've ever been good and and ever took seriously I know that alot of ya'll can relate to my music. I make alot of different kinds of music. I don't brag about the shit I've seen or done,but I put it on wax so the people with the same background can sleep thru the night. Fuck the fame. Like my page if you feel this shit,if not,scroll on down the page.
-Maniac


Born Terra Stolberg on September 23,1992. She was born and raised in Eureka,California. She was raised by a single mother who suffered with depression and at one time addiction. Her father was in and out of prison,suffering with alcholism and addiction.Maniac herself suffered with her own demons,even as a young child. Watching her mother suffer thru abusive boyfriends,who abused both her and her mother,had lasting effects on her. At one point Stolberg,her mother,her sister,and baby brother crammed into a small back room of grandma's house for a little over a year,untill Stolberg's mom rented a house in the Projects(slang for a bad neighborhood) With hip hop influences from her dad,and rock and alternitive influences form her mom,and a bit of her own music taste,she began to use music to excape her harsh realities. She could be seen constanly wearing headphones,during class,at home,or on the streets. Later that year her dad ran Boneyard Computers,which served more as a drug buisness than a computer buisness,her dad built her a computer with music programs in it.
