Mark Bolger is an American singer-songwriter and record producer. He has been a prolific musician for the majority of his life, having discovered his talent and passion for music at the age of six. Bolger began playing the piano by ear at this age and was quickly eager to explore other instruments including the guitar, saxophone and drums. He began honing his vocal skills at the age of twelve by following the styles of his favorite artists, who ranged from The Beatles to bands such as Van Halen, The Cure and Radiohead.

In school, Bolger was awarded 'Best Musician' for his performance and leadership skills in choirs, jazz bands, and personally formed music groups. His first recording studio experience was for a high school project, where he was presenting on composing and performing an original song. Bolger immediately became fascinated with the energy and creativity of the recording process.

Bolger continued to write and perform after high school and throughout college, releasing six original albums and performing alongside artists such as Better Than Ezra, Ryan Cabrera and Panic! At The Disco.

In 2008, Bolger was asked to write, perform and record a song that would be featured on an International Compilation for World Peace. The song âRay of Hopeâ was selected and presented to the former Israeli Prime Minister, Shimon Peres, during the 2008 Olympics in Beijing.

Bolger is currently writing and producing songs for Recording Artists, Film/TV, The Songs of Love Foundation (www.songsoflove.org) as well as his own Solo releases.

title: Stay
extra:
As a veteran side man on the Mid-Atlantic music scene, Bronson Wagner has helped anchor many bands as a bassist. Now, intent on focusing on his own music, the singer/songwriter has embarked on a project to release a string of singles showcasing some of his favorite work from the past 20 years.

"These sessions are the beginnings of what I hope is a prolonged burst of recording and releasing my music. I've selected a range of songs that cover the different styles I've explored over my writing career. The variety is a primary reason that I am not compelled to release an album per se. There will be no cohesive tone to songs written over such a long time span, so I am embracing the differences and treating each song as a separate entity."

For now, "The Earthlings" are anyone and everyone that will be guesting on the studio sessions. As the project progresses, a band will be assembled to play live shows.

Stay is pretty self-explanatory. Just check the lyrics...

title: Come On Get Your Groove On
?Pick Up the Pieces
extra:
If you made it this far, maybe you actually want to hear about my enthralling (read: typical) life. I grew up in San Gabriel, CA and attended Polytechnic School in Pasadena for 14 years. There I received a phenomenal music education starting in Pre-K. In third grade I joined choir and began playing the cello, and music has been my defining passion ever since.

In high school, I had become immersed in cello playing around 20 hours each week. During my freshman year, however, I began experiencing numbness in my fingers and was diagnosed with Hereditary Neuropathy with Liability to Pressure Palsies essentially ending my cello career.

Taking my focus off of cello, however, opened up new opportunities for me to explore singing, songwriting, and behind the scenes aspects of the music industry. I became very involved in musical theatre, and began writing music regularly while teaching myself basic skills in multiple instruments.

As a Freshman at USC, I entered the Music Industry program to pursue a career in music with some combination of law, live production and promotion, publishing, and/or songwriting. After winning 1st place in a freshman talent show, I realized that now was the best time of any to pursue performance. Though I have generally been categorized as a musical theatre singer, I decided that only meant that I needed to adjust my powerful stage voice to fit into my songs.

album: A Reality Music Movement: Inauguration; The New Beginning of AK Hip Hop's Role Model
title: Not a Rock Star
extra: AK is Hip Hop's new role model with his versatile lyrics and today's modern rhythms that gives a new motto to follow for today's youth. His music is uplifting, and invigorates his fans to leave behind the old ways of street life, and to embrace a new mindset of being yourself at all cost. Growing up, he was born the second oldest of four children, and resided in the infamous hill top homes projects in Dayton, Ohio. His music started out as a way to relieve the negativity of his hometown neighborhood. AK Hip Hop's Role Model developed a passion for roller-skating which helped him to understand the rhythmic patterns of music. The pure enjoyment of skating and riding the beat helped him engage in the challenge of adapting to sounds. He soon grew to embrace the lyrics of Tupac and the mind conscious Nas. AK Hip Hop's Role Model internalized these positive lyrical flows and realized that they were actually talking about what was going on in the world. He dedicates his passion to his mother who passed away when he was at a young age. Her death pushed him to grow up. AK Hip Hop's Role Model took his mother's words as encouragement and turned them into responsibility. He's a down to earth wise man, who places an extreme value on family. His hope is to become a positive role model for the youth who need someone and something they can look up to.

ASPHALT MESSIAH BIO:
Their musical diversity affords them a wide range of opportunities in several musical genres, and their ability to write specific music for set projects reflects their talents as songwriters and producers as well as performers. The many years of experience working within the music and entertainment industry stands as a testament to their own ability of survival as an Independent band. The members of Asphalt Messiah hail from different points of the country, but all bring something to the table collectively. This diversity has allowed them to create music that brings "ALL PEOPLE" to the same concert hall.

On May 15, 2012, Host Leila Ciancaglini of the television show "Hollywood Life", a syndicated television show in Los Angeles, CA featured LA Rock Band Asphalt Messiah. The show will be broadcast through the V-MAS Television Network which boosts an audience of 18-Million viewers in the US, Mexico and Puerto Rico. V-MAS is a Spanish language network launched to bring Latin American news and culture to Latin American homes within the US while at the same time bringing US news, entertainment and culture into the home in Latin America and other countries. V-MAS Television Network is the largest Spanish/English television network broadcasting from the United States. http://www.vmastv.com

"This is another great exposure opportunity for Asphalt Messiah" stated Kacy Jones, Founder & Lead Guitarist. We are looking to reach/include "everyone" in our movement, and this is yet another opportunity to do so. Our music video plays for "Don't Forget the Fallen" are growing daily and our non profit organization "Project: Don't Forget the Fallen" (www.dontforgetthefallen.org) is now receiving major support affiliates.

Asphalt Messiah: Unplugged performed on April 21, 2012 at the Talking Stick in Venice, CA where some of their performances were recorded. A live acoustic performance of "FALL BACK", one of their popular songs was video taped for promotional use, and went live on YouTube April 23, 2012. As of May 21, 2012, the video has received over 7,400 views on YouTube. www.youtube.com/watch?v=9srbDv3399A The show was a free performance sponsored and hosted by Tish "Tha" Dish Roberts and Kingston Roberts Media to benefit the impoverished children of Asia Pacific International and animals of Operation Blankets of Love. http://kingstonrobertsmedia.com/2012/04/04/asphalt-messiah-_-unplugged-the-emancipation-celebration-is-here

Asphalt Messiahs' "Don't Forget the Fallen" video released March 2012 has received over 112,300 views to date and counting. The video was released to honor the song of the same title released in July 2011. It is a tribute to military veterans and their families worldwide. www.youtube.com/watch?v=DGdKqixsX00 Be sure to visit the non-profit organization of Asphalt Messiah ("Project: Don't Forget the Fallen") that was designed to bring awareness and empowerment not only to Veterans of All Wars, but to their families as well. www.dontforgetthefallen.org

Asphalt Messiah has opened for Hip-Hop legend Warren G at Busbyâs in LA, head lined the Iron Circus, rocked the Marines "Toyâs for Tots" and played to a sold out crowd at the famous LA Whiskey A-Go-Go on the Sunset Strip, where they opened for the platinum recording group P.O.D. with Slash, The Smashing Pumpkins, and other well known artists in attendance and performing.
"Transform Me" by Asphalt Messiah was previously submitted to Paramount Pictures for inclusion in the "Transformer" trilogy and was a serious contender to be included in the movies. Asphalt Messiah was the only independent band at the table with such well known major acts as Nickelback, Green Day, Linkin Park and Cheap Trick. To review other press releases, music, shows and more visit the music site of Asphalt Messiah at www.reverbnation.com/asphaltmessiah

Through their association with AirPlay Direct and networking globally with their radio stations partners (especially their syndicated radio partners Westfield Recording Radio, WBLP Rock Dallas, Radio Gets Wild Europe,etc.), the music of Asphalt Messiah is being played in 15 different countries and has now started to build a radio fan base in Amsterdam. http://www.airplaydirect.com/www.airplaydirect.com/AsphaltMessiah

Just back from Nashville "Hot off the press" is Chris Keith's long awaited 4th CD "Churchman". Blues to Rock to a Chill, Jazz feel..Enjoy!

Chris Keith composes with his Nashville team. He has been working with this team for over 10 years. They are concentrating on thematic projects for TV and film.

Indie Nashville Songwriter / Recording Artist and Morro Bay California Worship Leader Chris Keith has 4 Cd's.
Hits songs off his 1st. Cd "He Took My Name To The Cross" are "Daddy Dance with Me" A popular Daddy Daughter wedding dance song played at wedding's across the country, the new "Butterfly Kisses" or "Cinderella". Written for his daughter Tayler when she was 3 years old, she pulled on his shirt saying "Daddy dance with me" A song was born. Also title song "He Took My Name To the Cross" The most inspired Easter song in this decade!

The 2nd Cd "Walkin'" has hit songs "I'm Afraid" written after Chris' son Jesse had 4 needless brain surgeries, because his wife Shelene was not given a simple $25 GBS test at 35 weeks of pregnancy. Chris and his family changed the law nationally. Now, every pregnant woman in the US is tested for GBS. www.theJesseCause.org
Also on the "Walkin' Cd is the "Sexy God song "Song of Songs" Chris wrote for Shelene on Valentine's Day.

The 3rd Cd "Knockin'" has hit songs "Mary's Baby" Played at churches and homes across America, it is the new "Mary did you know". And the touching 9/11 song "In America" shows that God still lives, and our flag still flies "In America". Like many fans across America; you will love and play Chris' Cd's over and over. Up lifting and Inspirational!

title: I'm Afraid
extra:
"I'm Afraid" written after Chris' son Jesse had 4 needless brain surgeries, because his wife Shelene was not given a simple $25 Group B Strep (GBS) test at 35 weeks of pregnancy. Chris and his family went on a national crusade to get every pregnant woman tested for GBS. They did not want any other family to go through what they had too. Chris and his family started the Jesse Cause-Saving the Babies from GBS named after Chris' son by performing concerts and passing out pamphlets. His fans became the causes army! It took them 5 years but they changed the law. Now, every pregnant woman in the US is tested for GBS at 35 weeks of pregnancy. Today Jesse Keith is a handsome and talented 15 year old. He is recorded his 1st. in Nashville called "One Dance" it is on itunes. He is following in his dad's footsteps...Chris is very proud of him and thanks God that he is alive!
see www.Chris Keith.com under "Jesse' story".

title: My OS is G.O.D.
extra:
Standard Deviation is one of the freshest acts to come onto the new music scene. Their sound is extremely energetic with an underlying intellectual depth not found in most new offerings.

The two performers/songwriters Â­- two time Billboard Songwriting contest award winners - are:

Jeff "Hands" Kozuch
Drums, Keyboards and Background Vocals

Jeff studied with Ralph Humphrey (Frank Zappa/PIT) and played the New Wave/Punk circuit with Dred Scott, The Alley Cats and Zamp Nicall; booked with bands like The Motels, The Go Gos, The Bangles, X, The Plimsouls and other artists. He also does public speaking for companies in the computer/MIDI industry such as Apple Computer and Passport Inc. He brings a unique creativity to the writing and recording processes.

Jane Lee
Vocals and Keyboards

Jane brings a fresh, energetic presence to the stage as she performs. Her intensity and professionalism are evident at every step of the writing, recording and performing processes. Jane studied voice with Seth Riggs, the reknowned vocal coach based in West Los Angeles. She also studied classical piano for 12 years and dance at California State University, Fullerton for 3 years. Jane's band experience includes fronting several bands, as both lead singer and keyboardist. Her vocals drive home the upbeat message in the theme song for Long Beach Carnaval, "Carnaval in Downtown Long Beach". Her driving positive energy makes her a natural.

title: Bedrock
extra: Not one to be boxed in, generalized, or easily summed up; Ashleigh Eymann is anything but a one-trick-pony. With music most naturally described as soul, Ashleigh fuses hip-hop, jazz, funk and blues into a mixed-bag supply creating a fresh hybrid of sound that makes pinning her down an impossibility. The roles of emcee, vocalist and multi-instrumentalist are here, guns blazing and passionately wrapped up in one chick.

extra:
About Liquid Tension Music:
Liquid Tension Music (LTM) is an independent label,songwriting/production team and studio. LTM collaborates with a variety of singers to produce original songs with cinematic quality that incorporates elements from various musical genres. LTM owns the master rights of its catalog and have the ability to respond quickly to music licensing opportunities.

About the featured artist:
Edrysse is an emerging young artist from Vancouver Canada. Only 14 years old, Edrysse already shows incredible talent in singing. In person, she is shy, reserved and quiet. But when she sings, her powerful voice can impact directly to the listener's heart and soul.Her ability to interpret the music is equally impressive. She is able to get into character in a way that drives home the original vision of the music. Her performance is both energetic and compassionate.

Godwin H. Barton, Canadian First Nations. A writer of poetry and prose, Godwin has published an inspirational story "Touched by a Higher Power" in the much acclaimed "Chicken Soup for the Soul" series. His poem, "An Eagle Powerfully in Flight" was published in the anthology "Island Skies," Canada. As well as being a passionate and devoted poet, he has also been referred to as a âMaster Storyteller.â Godwin, through readings and speaking engagements, shares his craft devotedly through various schools as well as Chapters and Indigo book stores. Godwin is pursuing a new dream as a singer-songwriter and has released his debut mini-album "Your Presence" under Liquid Tension Music.

About the featured artist:
A graduate of Berklee College of Music in 1980, David Bernstein formed the eclectic pop jazz band The David Bernstein Group, performed live from 1980-1984 and were featured on many television and radio shows across Canada. In 1985 David formed The Source. An '80's pop rock band that performed on television and radio and in top clubs across Canada. From 1985-1988, they received national Gold Rotation airplay on some well received records. David hung up his 'recording artist shoes' and concentrated on writing music for film and television in 1990. He continues to write award winning music for many Canadian productions. In 2004, David discovered a youthful passion in sharing his industry experience with young people. In addition to his writing projects, he currently teaches some industry related courses at Langara College and The Art Institute of Vancouver.

title: Grow Old With Me (John Lennon cover)
extra:
Written by John Lennon.
It has never been properly recorded by him, only as a demo and included on his 1983 posthumous album "Milk & Honey".
I recorded this in a dark and damp cellar in west Wales, as if it was an "Imagine" session in 1971... It could be as if Ringo were on drums, Klaus Voorman on bass, and Nicky Hopkins on Piano, of course there's a bit of Mellotron here and there...

title: NIGHTMARE IN RED
extra:
NIGHTMARE IN RED

Â© Cyrus Dali Vesuvala

...And this girl with the blonde hair in the shiny red raincoat
He'd followed in silent but desperate chase,
Had never turned round once, but he hoped that she looked good:
For, somehow, he just had to look at her face

Through roads and dark alleys, but always this dark night-
His mad world of nightmare had never known light-
And all was deep silence, except for the sound
Of her click-clacking high-heels, a-covering ground

She walked on in darkness, her gait was inviting
The shadow behind her, who was even now fighting
The beast that took over his mind and was tearing
His lips drawn back over teeth he was baring...

Her walk turns to hurrying, he can tell by the sound,
As he reaches the corner and races around,
She hears him behind her, her heart starts to pound,
But her shoes have turned traitor- she falls to the ground...

He sees her there lying alone in the rain-
She sees him and scrambles to get up again!
He sees her blind terror - his heart starts to race,
And he knows that he just has to touch her face...

There are tears in his eyes, as he reaches out-
There's a smile on his face, but no sound from his mouth-
She sinks her teeth into the arm of his coat
As she feels his fingers encircle her throat...

Warm blood on his hands, and he looks down, amazed!
But sees only red through this terrible haze-
You bit me, you b**** ! he cries out in pain,
And smashes her face, again and again

And again and again and again and again
And again and again and again...

Newspaper screams: the toll rises to four
Young girls in a month, and how many more?
Cop on the case in an interview notes
That this guy has a thing for young blondes in raincoats...

...And the girl with the blonde hair in the shiny black raincoat
He'd followed in silent, but desperate chase,
Had never turned round once, but he hoped that she looked good:
For, somehow, he just had to look at her faceâ¦

title: LIVING IN A POSTWAR DREAM
extra:
This song is the outcome of a collaboration back in 2009 with Billy Simons, a very talented young lyricist from the U.S.

Billy asked whether I'd be interested to write the music for these lyrics he had just written and perform the song.

I thought the lyric was extremely well written and ready for the music writer to take over, without having to make too many changes.

I hope I have been able to do some justice to Billy's very evocative lyric.

LIVING IN A POSTWAR DREAM

Lyrics: Billy Simons (c) 2009
Music and performance: (c) Cyrus Vesuvala 2009

Verse-1:

I dreamt that dream again last night
The one in which I'm dead
The scene is grainy black and white
But the blood is crimson red
See a cardinal on that snow white beach
On that cold and blustery day
And I watch with trepidation
As he turns and flies away

Verse- 2:

His red tail flutters in the wind
As he races 'cross the sky
And as the scene fades out to black
I open up my eyes
Within this strange reality
Precursor to the screams
That cardinal is always there
Embedded in my dreams

Chorus:

Living in a postwar dream
Where the fighting never ends
More terrifying 'cos I've lost sight
Of what I must defend
Living in a postwar dream
A lifetime on the mend
A lifetime on the mend

Verse- 3:

The beachfront's now deserted
Those soldiers, long since gone
Their orders cancelled years ago
But my battle rages on
I can still hear that moaning
It's a young boy face-down and
He convulses as he's drowning
In a pool of blood and sand

Verse-4:

So, everyday I agonize
About the here and now
Wondering how I'll set the stage
To take my final bow
It doesn't matter much to me
When and where the curtain falls
I've waited all these years to hear
That final bugle call

Bridge:

So, yearning for tomorrow
As today slips through my hands
I'm trapped within this hour glass
Half buried in the sands
At the beaches here at Normandy
Which never looked so grand...
Oh, the beaches here at Normandy
Are grand...
The beaches here at Normandy
Are grand...

title: DAVID AND GOLIATH (HAVE YOU EVER?)
extra:
In 2009, Dominic McPolin sent me a few lyics that he'd worked upon to see if I might be able to put any of them to music.
The lyric "David and Goliath" immediately struck a chord with me and I set about working on the music for it.
A couple of weeks later I rhad ecorded this: my first and only recording of that song.
A few weeks later, Abdulla Almahmeed made a very powerful video of the song.
The visuals of that video are very disturbing but convey the horror of war and its effect on children, powerfully.
Here is a link to that video:

https://picasaweb.google.com/117507100367131610920/DavidAndGoliathHaveYouEver?authuser=0&authkey=Gv1sRgCOzV1NHQoLKldw&feat=directlink

title: TRAMPLED ROSES
extra:
This song was written and composed over a period of two weeks in June 2009, as a collaboration with Michael Taub and Curtis Campbell, both from the USA, for a competition on the MusesMuse site. The aim of the competition was to compose an original song whose title and lyric theme had to be "Trampled Roses" .... As I recall, there were 8-10 entries, this was ours. It started off with Michael and Curtis being responsible for the lyric and me for the music and recording, but I got involved in the lyric process also, and this is how it all turned out...

TRAMPLED ROSES

Â© 2009
Lyrics : Michael Taub, Curtis Campbell, Cyrus Vesuvala
Music: Cyrus Vesuvala


I pick up trampled petals of the flowers
That I'd left the week before
And as I think of our last hours
And a future that's no more
I fight to swallow back the tears
And the pain this thought exposes
I know that you've been here all these years
I've been seeing those trampled roses...

Fell in love when we were little
Our love blossomed from the start
Initials etched into our tree
An arrow through a heart
I can still hear you call my name
Still hear your peals of laughter
It's just time I have a lot of
As I contemplate the thought of
This awful lonely long
Forever after...

Red trampled roses
My friends tell me you are gone
But I see those scattered roses
And I sense you here so strong
Red trampled roses
And I know that they're all wrong
Red, red, roses
Red trampled roses
You've been right here, all along...

Rosie I was stupid, drunk
And racing through the night
You were with me scared, I never saw
That turn it was too tight
I did you wrong, and while this song
May never make it right
My heart is once more racing
At the prospect that I'm facing
Soon, you can stop your pacing
Through the night

Red trampled roses
They all say that you are gone
I see those scattered roses
And I know that they're all wrong
Red trampled roses
I sense you here so strong
Red, red, roses
Red trampled roses
You've been watching, all along...

I pick up the petals of the flowers
That I'd left the week before...

title: Who is Who?
extra:
Liner Notes

This was my first Hollywood band fresh out of Musician's Institute/Guitar Institute of Technology and what a short strange trip is was! After playing enough gigs on The Sunset Strip, got signed to Rag Records and put in the studio. Unfortunately, the singer was a "Drugstore Cowboy" and we lost our contract. then the band broke up. Just another lost Hollywood story!

AutoBiography:

Eric Whited
Composer/Producer
WhitedOut@Gmail.com
323-336-3188

Classically trained on piano from the ages of 8-16 all the while white-knuckling performances in competitions at The Cleveland Music Settlement and The University of Akron. At age 11, in the Summer of 1978, I was a member of the Cleveland Orchestra Boy's Choir performing Carl Orff's "Carmina Burana" at Blossom Music and am hopeful this isnât my only 15 minutes of fame in life. Got my first electric guitar from a garage sale at age 16 and taught myself how to play Stairway to Heaven since it just didn't sound right on piano.

After completing two years at Thee Ohio State University's School of Music, decided to move to Hollywood, California in July of 1989 and graduated from Musician's Institute/Guitar Institute of Technology - actually quite an accomplishment considering the vast majority didn't. Was signed to Rag Records with my band, The Mustard Seeds and as a producer for the band, Treehouse Toys for Planet Earth Records. While on Planet Earth, played at the first anniversary of 9/11 for a benefit promoted by KROQ. Even licensed Music to Playboy Entertainment for their cable channel that gave me a certain infamous reputation around town. Took my first stab at composing to film when I composed Title and Credit Cues for the Independent Film, "Man's Best Friend" (Maxwell Productions). Signed a Development Deal with the Entertainment Law Firm, Madison Law Group (my first dealing with entertainment lawyers) and produced a ballad for recording artist, Satori. Signed a Development Deal with Cornerstone Studios (Fleetwood Mac, Motley Crue) to produce vocalist, Tami Johnson. Went back to school at UCLA Extension School's Film Scoring Certificate Program and composed for Chamber Orchestras, Small Ensembles, Quintets, Quartets, and Trios that I do consider my greatest educational experience to date.

In May of 2003, I moved back to The FarEast Side of Cleveland, Ohio because of a family tragedy and created WhitedOut Productions & Studio on Murray Hill producing seven Cds for commercial release including Jim Millerâs double CD, In-Trance-It: an absolute thrill since I have been following him since Oroboros. Considering the fact that my recording studio was in an art gallery building, performed live at Murray Hill Art Walks, SPARX Gallery Hops, and Fashion Shows. Performed with vocalist, Susan Fletcher at The Abbey Road on the River Festival in Louisville, KY and Louise Harrison, George's sister, complimented us for our version of "Imagine". Got back into Film/Television composing and contributed music to the Cleveland-based television series, "Out of Darkness" including the Main Theme (see YouTube interview above). Then went on to produce the Cd entitled, "HARP ROCK" for Harpist, Christina Kline performing 14 Classic Rock standards that never sound so serene. Also produced Christina's harp version of ZZ Topâs, âGimme All Your Lovinâ â for the FOX Television show, âBONESâ and learned a lot about The Industry through dealings with Fox's Music division. Was thrilled when Northern Ohio Live Magazineâs television show, âLive from the Circleâ used my song, "Cool Jazz for Ma'" for their main theme for a 13 week run on PBS. Played solo two years in a row at the Let's Get Together Festival in a natural amphitheater in Central, PA and have decided playing at outdoor music festivals is the way to go.

And now I have moved back to Hollywood, Cali to promote my music to Vocalists/Lyricists and Film & Television.

extra: I had so much fun making this I cant stand it. First I played the drums on my piano keyboard; kicks with my thumbs, snares and hi hats with my index, middle and ring fingers and rides with my pinkies. Then I added the roto toms, also played with my fingers. Then I improvised over the drums with my midi guitar triggering the bass and piano while also recording the guitar itself. Then I took the whole piano part and transposed it up a fourth...

extra: "Lush Life" is a jazz standard with lyrics and music written by Billy Strayhorn from 1933 to 1938. It is usually performed in the key of D-flat major.

extra:
Award-winning Adele-Marina Wilding is a multi-talented singer/songwriter, composer/arranger and pianist. Previously based in England and Scotland, she paid her dues on the UK music scene, where she established herself as a respected, crossover singer/songwriter. Having begun her professional singer-songwriter career eight years ago, Adele-Marina has released three self-produced, commercial CDs: Emeralds (& Other Little Gems) (2004, Blue Dawn Records), Sketches On Blue: Limited Edition EP (2005, Blue Dawn Records) and Portholes & Skylights: Limited Edition EP (2009, ProdiGal Records). Tracks from all three releases have resulted in excellent reviews and airplay/appearances on national and international radio.

Born in Colchester, England to a Barbadian mother and an English father, and raised in Canada and Europe, Adele-Marina is a classically trained pianist and contralto. Her formative influences include Robert Schumann and French Impressionist composers Claude Debussy and Gabriel Faure. Adele-Marinaâs musical training culminated in the Diploma in Jazz and Popular Music Studies (performance, composition and arranging) from the renowned Goldsmiths College, University of London. She has since performed in premiere venues in the UK and Canada: the Jazz CafÃ©, Rhythm & Muse, the Hackney Empire Bullion Room, the Troubadour Club, Biddle Bros (London), Rockers (Glasgow), Lady of the Lake, Samâs Place (Canada), among many others. UK highlights include solo and duo appearances at the Vortex Jazz Club, London, and performances at the Tavistock Music & Arts Festival, Devon (2006) and the Edinburgh Fringe (2009).

UK awards/accolades include inaugural Winner of the BWA Nina Simone Award 2005 (for which she was again nominated in 2008), Semi Finalist in the UK Songwriting Contest (2006/07) and invited Performer at the NME/Uncut Artist Showcase in Central London (2009).

An emerging, instrumental composer, Adele-Marinaâs classical pieces have been performed by the pro Edinburgh chamber group Red Note Ensemble at the Traverse Theatre Bar, Edinburgh and at The Arches, Glasgow. Her works have been well received by audience members and the press. She was also one of five, UK based composers who were selected for the âNoisy Wordsâ Composer/Playwright event in November 2010 at the Traverse Theatre.

title: JL Wright WPMD radio feature
extra:
The Mo Power & Carol Tatum Radio Hour

Unsigned Artists from Around the World

Tuesday 4pm-5pm

title: Idols
extra:
I don't believe in idols anymore I'm old enough to have seen their altars crumble. I don't think the way I did back then, I'd be ashamed but i was caught up in revival.

I dont know what happens after this nor do they but theyll sell you on a floor plan, follow the the exit signs the plan is clear while the smoke and fire heat up all around you.

They called on the wrath of God, to settle a damn Petty dispute, it's hard to believe they didn't get their wish but I don't think god had anything to do with it.

Seems like everyone we ever looked up to sooner or later found themselves looking down, we learned long ago not to make idols out of gold but still learning not to make them out of men.

I don't carry a cross anymore someone else said they lighten my burden, it's funny how we say that love will surely win while they say we will surely burn for it.

title: Treasures
extra:
Set off on another adventure, like your seeking treasure that could fill up your heart
How long have you been on this journey, now you still feel the yearning you did at the start.

Slow down take a breathe like you take a drag, even though you quiet that dirty habit some time ago, know that everything must fade glory, gold, and the profane but love will remain.

When you finally find that treasure make sure that you hide it where death will not find, it's better to put your pleasure in the things that outlast time.

Wear your heart out, wear your heart out it's out there anyway.

title: Zealot Kid
extra:
Man your such a zealot kid yeah you got it all figured out. And your gonna set the world on fire you wouldnt hide it or put it out.

All you want is a chance to say your credible enough, all you want is a chance but man their gonna rough you up.

Your not gonna get there I not how you thought you would

You take your hits kid and you keep moving on, you were told this was coming but it still takes it's toll

All you wanted was a chance to see if you were tough enough. All you wanted was a chance but yeah their gonna fuck you up

Call yourself a preacher but you would darken the door, and there's no place that'll have you cause you know what you stand for.

All you wanted was a chance to express what you thought, all you wanted was a chance but man their gonna rough you up.

And your gonna get there but not like you thought you would.

title: Rapture Drug
extra:
Just another day the world was suppose to end... The radio preacher is hanging his head.. While his listeners prepare for the end.. But it's all a rapture drug..it's all a rapture drug..
The sense is there's something in the air, and time is short, but the ending has to matter, for the rest of it to make sense.

But there were signs There where signs..There are signs...

Seven seals are breaking, the earth is shaking, the weather changing, the profits loosing, the nations are watching to see who will make the first move, need an escape when you've got nothing to loose.. The rapture is a drug.. The rapture is a drug.

title: Judges
extra:
There was a time I hit the floor, The room was overwhelmed
The pleasure shook me down
There was a presence there.

never stayed for long, I couldn't ask you to, but I felt so upside down without your presence there.

I saw you beat her sickness as you wrapped her in your arms, we thought we we're judges but clearly we were wrong.

Never stayed for long, I couldn't ask you to, but it never felt the same without your presence there.

The edges were all altered
The limits now unbound
I watched the resurrection
Spring life up all around

I thought I saw it clearly
i know I missed allot
We all wanted to be judges
but a judges we are not.

title: Fair Fight
extra:
We found the fight was thrown before we even got, and I tried to jump the fence, that's how i got these scars, I knew the garden was somewhere back there, well I looked but it was not found

They said for my offennses I would burn forever, even though I was only there a short time, when would I find my love they said I would never, that's when i knew for it wasn't a fair fight.

They say you will have to choose a color, but from my birth I was always blind. My choses will follow me forever, even thought only have a limited time.

And I will tell you all the truth I know, while I stand here, if you don't know love you don't know anything at all, all of this might sound like a cliche, but love is a fight thrown before it even starts.

title: Catch Your Breath
extra:
I went up to the mountain to rest for a time, the wind starting blowing but the lord I did not find

I went up to the mountain to see behind the lies the earth started shaking but the lord I did not find.

I went up to the mountain try to clear my mind a fire came down from heaven but the lord i did not find

I sat down on the mountain to let it all sink in, and there in simple silence truth came loud and clear

If your looking for sensation this earth has enough, but if your looking for salvation you have to catch your breath

it's a piece of dust on fire burns brighter than the starts, and earth wind and fire can get us all bothered , if your looking for sensation this world has a enough, but if your looking for salvation you'll have to catch your breath.

title: Danny
extra:
Danny you won't seem to let it go
how long will you wait like a snake in the road
Your toungue speaks of all the need that we have, but your bite makes us all take a step back

I feel I fear it's gonna be another long year, cause your breaking your promise. It's not going unoticed. I feel I fear, ever though you may shed no tears your still wating to be delivered. We're all waiting to be delievered.

Danny we still all got your back, but you won't seem to let us make the catch. Sure you can be the judge. A wiser man there never was.

I feel what you feel

I want what you want

Cry for just to feel your thrills
Ask for privilege to cure your ills

the setting is fake

everyone is all dressed up for
someone and someplace I've never been before

Like an explosive payload

extra:
www.facebook.com/StaticParallel

Static Parallel creates a captivating and riveting sound, a distinct Northwest rock style that will pierce through your soul and leave you craving more.

When Static Parallel's Rovski and J-Vandal first got together, there was an immediate music connection rooted in the traditional hard-hitting greats of yesteryear. After creating a signature melodic hard-rock parallel of guitar- and bass-driven songwriting structure, they were ready to build the band that together would define their collective vision, with the intention of pushing rock-and-roll ever forward. Cementing the instrumental foundation on drums, Fast Lane keeps the pace and ties in tight with the bass lines, leaving no doubt about the band's influences while charting new sonic territories. SP's compelling aural dimensions culminate in Aaron Burnett's vocal mastery - with the range and style indicative of the pioneers of rock but adding unrelenting elements of the Now - from deft subtlety to outright aggression.

The vision fulfilled, Static Parallel is complete, and the set list is sure to please true rock fans. The source is Northwest, the feel is Rock and Roll.

The band is currently rehearsing new material for an album-length recording.

"You know how you come across the most absolutely perfect person; you find them some way somehow? There's a perfect alignment in every way possible-physically, emotionally, spiritually. But for some unknown reason you just can't get together. That's what Static Parallel means, two energies moving in the same direction but never connecting, epic tragedy but a universal truth."
A playful upbeat song about missing someone
A short song about never having enough time
A Stupid Song about Stupid People
A song about Living The Hollywood Dream

title: Got Dat Glow - Radio
extra: Life has not always been sweet for this 27-year old Nigerian born, Urban/Pop & Hip-Hop recording artist. Eteka, now lives in Toronto, Canada and is launching his solo career to create a new wave of music, a sound mixed with hip-hop and African flavor. His love for music began when he was a child. Music became an escape, a place he could go to dismiss the terrible memories of childhood that he now resents. When asked about his childhood, he would say it was a life full of hard labor and abuse. He recalls being deprived of the basic necessities that we all need in life. To manage and survive abuse in Nigeriaâs poverty-stricken environment, he had to mature quickly. After migrating to Canada, Eteka found himself on the wrong side of the track. At 19, he started selling drugs and running the streets to make a living. It wasnât long before he was charged for a crime that led him 120 days of community service and 17 weeks in an anger management program. Upon his release, he was stranded and having nowhere to go or any family support became homeless. He later rebounded and began performing in clubs and bars hoping someone would take notice of his talent. He auditioned for Canadian Idol, but dropped out, deciding it wasnât for him. In 2005, Eteka and a friend he met at the Canadian Idol formed the group, St. Eves. Under record labels, Attack Group/Universal, they released their debut album âAll That I Needâ. The group went their separate ways in 2008 with Eteka striking out on his own. Today, Eteka is signed to Atlanta based Sereniti Records and will soon be releasing his debut single, âGot Dat Glowâ. The single has an upbeat flow and tasteful lyrics that are catchy. Eteka plans on using his musical platform to become an advocate for children in Nigeria, who have witnessed and experienced abuse and enslavement.

title: No one is really getting out
extra:
I write pop, dance/electronia and R&B songs. I like to blend new style into my music and try various kinds of arrangement.

I have only started to produce music for about a year, but my songs have catchy melodies, fun rhythmic beats and great originality.

Currently I don't live in the US ( I am living in China). I am hoping that I can have a job at a US record label as a songwriter, music arranger, and back ground singer. Still, my best hope is to get a record deal.

My future plan is to go to US next year, and play live show and sell CD myself. Still, I am improving my production skills and vocal skills and all other kinds of music skills.

Over the last 25 years, Craig has written over 40 songs that reflect a variety of styles, tempos, and themes. He draws much of his inspiration from his work as a residential builder, his family, life, and from God. His mission is to write unique, inspirational music that also kicks butt in the music charts.

Craig lives southeast of Nashville in Middle Tennessee. Over the last 15 years he has spent his time refining and demoing his song collection, and now feels ready to take his songs to market.

Crystal Ship is an independent project that aims to get away of labels and fashions of the moment.
The mix between old and new electronics and the fusion of styles (from the more classic metal to more intimate synthetic music) creates a multitude of images and stimuli that excite and incite.
This is the Crystal ShipÂ´s challenge: to promote a personal reaction and ever different, as a result of the personal map that each listener builds from an active listening. Music for protagonists!

Iâm a composer and an interpreter. I've been playing bass for over 14 years and experiencing the possibilities of keyboard and synthesizer for 7 years.
Since 2010 Iâm professionally qualified with a master's degree in music production achieved at microFusa in Barcelona.
Crystal Ship is my first independent project.

title: Radio Up
extra:
messages from some of todayâs very best family musicians.

After the January 12th, 2010 earthquake that destroyed much of the Haitian capital, family musician wj found himself feeling helpless and desperately wanting to help the people of Haiti. Having close friends in Haiti and feeling a deep love and respect for the music from the region, ELIZABETH BAYARD felt the need to create something that could help the ongoing rebuilding effort.

Anesthetic & the Withdrawal
extra:
âOne Last Monsoonâ was primarily recorded in the songwriterâs (David Abraham) bedroom - an apt environment for an album, which essentially sounds like a love letter to the Indie & Alternative genres from a boy who spends his time locked up in a room with his countless records. Each song, layered in rich melodies and gorgeous harmonies, hints at an ever-growing list of artists spanning from almost every sub-genre of Alternative/Indie imaginable.

A few that come to mind: Matt Pond, Feeder, Tokyo Police Club, 31 Knots, Soundgarden, the Stills, Team Sleep, Drill Team, Chevelle, Noel Gallagher, Longwave, Minus the Bear, the Foals, Hey Mercedes, Stone Temple Pilots, Swervedriver, the French Kicks. The debut album from The Koniac Net not only pays tribute to these artists, but at the same time breathes new life into the Indie genre. âOne Last Monsoonâ is for all intent and purposes a mixed tape for the Indie music fan; a goodie bag in which the listener is rewarded each time they choose to reach in for something familiar but new.

title: Dirty Diamonds-Lets Get Loud
extra:
Dirty Diamonds are a five piece Hard Rock band based in Limerick, Ireland. Influenced by the glamour of 80's Metal and the hard edged attitude of 90's Rock they blend big hooks with balls out Rock n' Roll. They are known for their catchy songs and highly energetic live shows.

Dirty Diamonds are set to release their debut E.P. "Leaving Town" in August 2012 and are currently playing shows around Ireland and the U.K. in support of it. Recording has also begun in Bow Lane Studios, Dublin on their debut album "Let's Get Loud!" which is set for an early 2013 release.

Dirty Diamonds was formed in late summer 2009 and after a couple of stop-gap guitarists the full line up was cemented in 2011. The goal from the outset was to write balls out Rock n' Roll songs with big chourses and screaming guitar solos. With "Leaving Town" Dirty Diamonds have achieved just that. Aswell as recording their debut E.P. in 2011, Dirty Diamonds supported such acts as Warrior Soul, Crashdiet and The Answer, winning over new fans along the way.
2012 is set to be "The Year Of The Diamond" with Dirty Diamonds setting their sights on the U.K. and Europe and expanding their ever growing base of fans or "Diamondites"

title: Excelsior School Anthem
extra:
Bruce Berghâs newest 2012 release, âNight Lifeâ is a collection of original âRat-Packâ tunes written during 2011 as a nightlife entertainer in some of Chicagoâs finest dining establishments. Bergh performs on piano with vocal stylings in the Pop, Rock and Jazz Vocal genres. As a composer, he strives for memorable melody lines accompanied by jazz harmonizations with a positive message.

Bergh studied at Sherwood Music School and the University of Chicago, and has written hundreds of songs, commercial music and jingles, as well as arranged music for a large number of clients through the years at his three recording studios. As a professor of Music Technology, Bergh taught in four universities, done clinician work for MTNA, MENC, and NAMM conventions, and founded The Bergh Institute of Music Technology (BIMT.net and DrMIDI.com).

Some of Berghâs career highlights include playing organ for the Chicago Cubs at Wrigley Field, performing live with Kerry Livgren of âKansasâ on synthesizer, pianist/vocalist for Willow Creek Community Chapel events, traveling North America as a product specialist and clinician for numerous musical instrument manufacturers, collaborating with Bob Moog & Ray Kurzweil regarding synthesizer technology and sales, and leading worship and performing in many top churches, theaters and convention centers across the United States.


Bruce Berghâs Discography:

"25 Songs of Summer" compilation album released by Tunecore on iTunes Memorial Day 2012

âNight Lifeâ a CD collection of new âRat-Packâ styled and pop originals released April 28, 2012

âTaxi Portfolio 2011â is an eclectic collection of tunes written for Taxi A&R in 2011

âChristmas Time of the Yearâ a CD collection of Christmas originals released in November 2011

âChristmas Time of the Yearâ a single released on iTunes 2010

âFamily Albumâ a CD collection of music written about his family released in 2010 as an Independent Artist

âParadiseâ a CD collection of original Contemporary Christian (CCM) songs released in 2009 by BIMT Studios.

âBody Language: An Excercise in Excessive Sampling Abuseâ a 45 single released in 1988 by Rednose Records (Flip side of "Dubois Boys")

"Dubois Boys" a Novelty Polka 45 RPM single released in 1988 by Rednose Records

Found In You (extended version)
extra:
The Artist
Barry Johnson's music is a big plate of rock-infused rhythms and drive with a healthy pinch of soul, slathered with a heaping helping of gospel-inspired ingredients like B3 organ, thick background vocals, and altar-call-wailing guitars.

The Album â Tenacious Grace
Co-produced by legendary Allman Brothers audio guru Bud Snyder, Barry's latest CD "Tenacious Grace" is steeped in all the classic rock guitar tones and soul-beckoning B3 organ youâd expect from Snyderâs influence.

The Influences
Fans have compared Barry's music to the likes of John Mayer, One Republic, Eric Clapton, Santana and Steve Winwood. Guess they couldn't make up their minds.

The Venues and Legends
Living in Europe and traveling the world has allowed Barry to perform in a lot of interesting venues; including Dutch National television, Belgian National radio, South East Asian refugee camps, and stages and streets all over Europe and the US. He has played along side legendary Gospel singer Jessie Dixon, CCM artists Tommy Walker and Karen Lafferty, and The Allman Bros. guitarist Dan Toler.

The Back Story
At 11 years old while living in Tulsa, Barry's folks bought him his first guitar; a red hollow body Rickenbacker knock-off. Played it through a small Kalamazoo 12 inch speaker amp. He studied under a local country music artist, learning all the hits. After a couple of years the family moved to Florida. Barry parked the guitar to the side for the drums, which his dad bought from a starving University of Florida student. It was a Ludwig kit with a white pearl finish and some great Zildjian cymbals. But all the while he'd pick up his guitar and keep at it.

A few years later at the age of 15, Barry started playing and singing in church bands and vocal ensembles, performing for churches, youth groups, prisons and various state facilities throughout Florida, some even as far away as England. This was the catalyst that inspired Barry to move overseas, eventually to Amsterdam, Holland where he lived for several years, touring throughout Europe, Thailand and the US.

title: Going East
extra:
See more at www.facebook.com/cottonwinemusic!!
Guess we have everything to owe to this song, 'Going East'. Without it, there would be no Cotton Wine. We wrote this song on our driving trip across the US from Los Angeles to Nashville in our car, thinking it was a cool song about our life changing experiences. So we took a video of us singing it in the car while we were driving, posted it to our Facebook walls to share with friends and the seed was planted.
We hope you enjoy this first song of ours as much as we do.
Thank you for your support.
Sincerely,
Cotton Wine
Brandon & Femke

title: We Don't Mind Tonight
extra:
Raised is the San Francisco Bay Area. Colleen Sweeney
is the middle child of five children and the daughter of a piano teacher.
She began writing and playing guitar at 16.
She was influenced by such artists as Tori Amos.Joni Mitchell and Carole King.
She is completing her second album and will begin her third.
She currently lives in Templeton CA with her son Dillon where she is playing in local venues.
